{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780727695816,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_urqbKRCenu0UP2MSUIdapF97","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"POST /search|/search|Recall|Search|semantic|hybrid","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","include":"README.md"},"output":"Found 21 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md:\n  Line 109: > Without any AI keys the stack still starts — dummy providers return non-semantic embeddings, useful for testing the API surface.\n\n  Line 172: # Search for it\n\n  Line 173: curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/search \\\n\n  Line 261: - **Hybrid search** — pgvector semantic similarity + full-text keyword matching + knowledge graph expansion (up to 2 hops), ranked by composite score of similarity, importance, freshness, and graph boost\n\n  Line 263: - **Contradiction detection** — RDF triple comparison + LLM semantic analysis detects conflicting memories and automatically supersedes them, with full contradiction chain tracking\n\n  Line 275: - **Document store** — structured JSONB collections alongside semantic memories for exact-field lookups (customer records, config, task lists)\n\n  Line 283: |  | LoCoMo | LongMemEval | Search latency |\n\n  Line 339: | `memclaw_recall` | Hybrid semantic + keyword recall with graph-enhanced retrieval; optional LLM brief |\n\n  Line 342: | `memclaw_doc` | Document CRUD: `write`, `read`, `query`, `delete`, `list_collections`, `search` (semantic) on named JSON collections |\n\n  Line 351: > **Skill sharing** is now done via `memclaw_doc` — agents share a `SKILL.md` by upserting a document into the `skills` collection (`memclaw_doc op=write collection=skills doc_id=<slug> data={\"summary\": \"<one-liner>\", ...}`). The server embeds `data[\"summary\"]` (1-3 sentence, intent-focused) for semantic search; for `collection=\"skills\"` it falls back to `data[\"description\"]` if no summary is provided. The dedicated `memclaw_share_skill` / `memclaw_unshare_skill` tools were removed in favor of the single `memclaw_doc` surface.\n\n  Line 450: **Defaults:** `CORE_STORAGE_ROLE=hybrid` and `CORE_STORAGE_READ_URL=\"\"` — both null-safe, so single-node deploys need zero configuration to get the legacy single-service behavior.\n\n  Line 470:   Re-embedding is required; until rows are re-embedded, semantic search returns\n\n  Line 508:      write that touches them. Search will return empty results for cold rows\n\n  Line 596: | `/search` | POST | Hybrid semantic + keyword search with graph-enhanced retrieval |\n\n  Line 597: | `/recall` | POST | Search + LLM summarization — returns context paragraph + source memories |\n\n  Line 764: │       ├── pipeline/              # Composable write/search pipelines\n\n  Line 802: Write latency is dominated by LLM enrichment. Recall latency by the embedding API call.\n\n  Line 824: | `memclaw_recall` | Hybrid semantic + keyword search over memories, with optional LLM-summarised brief. |\n\n  Line 827: | `memclaw_list` | Non-semantic enumeration with filters, sort, cursor pagination. |\n\n  Line 837: > Skill sharing uses the generic `memclaw_doc` surface — write/read/query/search/delete on `collection=\"skills\"`. The server validates the slug and embeds `data[\"summary\"]` for semantic discovery (with a back-compat fallback to `data[\"description\"]` for skills).\n\n  Line 845: | Memory | `GET/POST /memories`, `PATCH /memories/{id}`, `DELETE /memories/{id}`, `PATCH /memories/{id}/status`, `POST /memories/bulk`, `POST /memories/bulk-delete`, `GET /memories/stats`, `GET /memories/{id}`, `GET /memories/{id}/contradictions`, `POST /search`, `POST /recall`, `POST /ingest/preview`, `POST /ingest/commit` |\n","metadata":{"matches":21,"truncated":false},"title":"POST /search|/search|Recall|Search|semantic|hybrid","time":{"start":1780727695805,"end":1780727695816}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_014107e689df4e0b016a23bf8fa9f88191b664b6fec133410b"}},"id":"prt_e9ba449ae001UgwLS5SdIjr8V1","sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","messageID":"msg_e9ba42091001HCIZhMHff53VOt"}}
