{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780727706099,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_uHMYdUBOY67rfFPAGjsXDPsp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","offset":588,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n588: | `/memories` | GET | List memories (filter by type, status, agent; paginate) |\n589: | `/memories/{id}` | GET | Full memory detail (embedding stats, entity links, RDF triple, temporal bounds) |\n590: | `/memories/{id}` | PATCH | Update content or metadata. Re-embeds if content changes |\n591: | `/memories/{id}` | DELETE | Soft delete (sets status to `deleted`) |\n592: | `/memories/{id}/status` | PATCH | Update lifecycle status |\n593: | `/memories/{id}/contradictions` | GET | View contradiction chain |\n594: | `/memories` | DELETE | Bulk soft-delete |\n595: | `/memories/stats` | GET | Counts by type, agent, and status |\n596: | `/search` | POST | Hybrid semantic + keyword search with graph-enhanced retrieval |\n597: | `/recall` | POST | Search + LLM summarization — returns context paragraph + source memories |\n598: | `/ingest/preview` | POST | Extract 5-20 atomic facts from a URL or text (no writes) |\n599: | `/ingest/commit` | POST | Write previewed facts as memories |\n600: \n601: </details>\n602: \n603: <details>\n604: <summary>Knowledge graph endpoints</summary>\n605: \n606: | Endpoint | Method | Description |\n607: |---|---|---|\n608: | `/entities` | GET | List entities (filter by type, search) |\n609: | `/entities/upsert` | POST | Create or update entity |\n610: | `/entities/{id}` | GET | Entity detail with relations and linked memories |\n611: | `/relations/upsert` | POST | Create or update relation |\n612: | `/graph` | GET | Full knowledge graph (entities + relations) |\n613: \n614: </details>\n615: \n616: <details>\n617: <summary>Evolve, Insights, Agents, Crystallizer, Documents, Fleet, Admin</summary>\n618: \n619: **Karpathy Loop / Evolve**\n620: \n621: | Endpoint | Method | Description |\n622: |---|---|---|\n623: | `/evolve/report` | POST | Report an outcome (success/failure/partial) against recalled memories |\n624: \n625: **Insights**\n626: \n627: | Endpoint | Method | Description |\n\n(Showing lines 588-627 of 965. Use offset=628 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| `/memories` | GET | List memories (filter by type, status, agent; paginate) |\n| `/memories/{id}` | GET | Full memory detail (embedding stats, entity links, RDF triple, temporal bounds) |\n| `/memories/{id}` | PATCH | Update content or metadata. Re-embeds if content changes |\n| `/memories/{id}` | DELETE | Soft delete (sets status to `deleted`) |\n| `/memories/{id}/status` | PATCH | Update lifecycle status |\n| `/memories/{id}/contradictions` | GET | View contradiction chain |\n| `/memories` | DELETE | Bulk soft-delete |\n| `/memories/stats` | GET | Counts by type, agent, and status |\n| `/search` | POST | Hybrid semantic + keyword search with graph-enhanced retrieval |\n| `/recall` | POST | Search + LLM summarization — returns context paragraph + source memories |\n| `/ingest/preview` | POST | Extract 5-20 atomic facts from a URL or text (no writes) |\n| `/ingest/commit` | POST | Write previewed facts as memories |\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>Knowledge graph endpoints</summary>\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","text":"| `/memories` | GET | List memories (filter by type, status, agent; paginate) |\n| `/memories/{id}` | GET | Full memory detail (embedding stats, entity links, RDF triple, temporal bounds) |\n| `/memories/{id}` | PATCH | Update content or metadata. Re-embeds if content changes |\n| `/memories/{id}` | DELETE | Soft delete (sets status to `deleted`) |\n| `/memories/{id}/status` | PATCH | Update lifecycle status |\n| `/memories/{id}/contradictions` | GET | View contradiction chain |\n| `/memories` | DELETE | Bulk soft-delete |\n| `/memories/stats` | GET | Counts by type, agent, and status |\n| `/search` | POST | Hybrid semantic + keyword search with graph-enhanced retrieval |\n| `/recall` | POST | Search + LLM summarization — returns context paragraph + source memories |\n| `/ingest/preview` | POST | Extract 5-20 atomic facts from a URL or text (no writes) |\n| `/ingest/commit` | POST | Write previewed facts as memories |\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>Knowledge graph endpoints</summary>\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/entities` | GET | List entities (filter by type, search) |\n| `/entities/upsert` | POST | Create or update entity |\n| `/entities/{id}` | GET | Entity detail with relations and linked memories |\n| `/relations/upsert` | POST | Create or update relation |\n| `/graph` | GET | Full knowledge graph (entities + relations) |\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>Evolve, Insights, Agents, Crystallizer, Documents, Fleet, Admin</summary>\n\n**Karpathy Loop / Evolve**\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/evolve/report` | POST | Report an outcome (success/failure/partial) against recalled memories |\n\n**Insights**\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Description |","lineStart":588,"lineEnd":627,"totalLines":965,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","time":{"start":1780727706081,"end":1780727706091}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05de074048d0847f016a23bf99f01c8191a315237430d8905c"}},"id":"prt_e9ba471df001mgtF37cscHWoJY","sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","messageID":"msg_e9ba44c4d0018BIWxCBC1Pg1is"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780727706099,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Rznh3zlAmDqEom3bF25ZuKPl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","offset":258,"limit":95},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n258: ### Memory Pipeline\n259: \n260: - **Single-pass LLM enrichment** — every write auto-classifies into one of 14 memory types, generates title/summary/tags, scores importance, flags PII, and extracts entities — from a single `content` field\n261: - **Hybrid search** — pgvector semantic similarity + full-text keyword matching + knowledge graph expansion (up to 2 hops), ranked by composite score of similarity, importance, freshness, and graph boost\n262: - **Live knowledge graph** — people, orgs, locations, and concepts extracted into entities and relations on every write. Semantic entity resolution (>0.85 cosine) auto-merges duplicates\n263: - **Contradiction detection** — RDF triple comparison + LLM semantic analysis detects conflicting memories and automatically supersedes them, with full contradiction chain tracking\n264: \n265: ### Self-Improving Memory\n266: \n267: - **Outcome-based learning (Karpathy Loop)** — agents report success/failure after acting on recalled memories; the system reinforces what works and auto-generates preventive `rule`-type memories on failure\n268: - **Crystallization** — LLM merges near-duplicate memories into canonical atomic facts with full provenance; 8-status lifecycle automation retires stale data\n269: - **Per-agent retrieval tuning** — each agent optimizes its own retrieval profile (top_k, min_similarity, graph_max_hops, blend weights) from feedback, so search quality compounds with every interaction\n270: \n271: ### Integrations\n272: \n273: - **MCP server** — built-in [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io) at `/mcp` (Streamable HTTP). Connect Claude Desktop, Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, or any MCP client with a URL and API key\n274: - **Multi-provider LLM** — primary + fallback provider chain per tenant (OpenAI, Gemini, Anthropic, OpenRouter) with platform defaults for zero-config tenants\n275: - **Document store** — structured JSONB collections alongside semantic memories for exact-field lookups (customer records, config, task lists)\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## Performance\n280: \n281: Benchmarked against the two most-cited public agent-memory benchmarks. Methodology and operator-scale context live in [`docs/performance.md`](docs/performance.md); the full write-up is on the blog.\n282: \n283: |  | LoCoMo | LongMemEval | Search latency |\n284: |---|---|---|---|\n285: | Accuracy (LLM-judge) | **77.6%** | **72.5%** | — |\n286: | Token savings vs full context | **96.6%** | **98.2%** | — |\n287: | Latency | — | — | **23 ms p50 · 27 ms p95** |\n288: \n289: Accuracy sits inside the leading cluster across the field (Mem0, Zep, MemClaw — scores cluster in a narrow band). The axes we push hardest are latency and token efficiency, because those are the ones that compound as agent count grows — a few hundred ms of search latency disappears behind one LLM call, but bills millions of times a day across a fleet.\n290: \n291: > Single-agent benchmarks can't measure cross-agent recall, outcome propagation between agents, fleet-scoped visibility, or governance-aware retrieval. Those are the questions that decide whether a memory system is *deployable* inside a company. See [`docs/performance.md`](docs/performance.md#what-these-benchmarks-cant-measure).\n292: \n293: Source: [Fast, Token-Efficient, and Built for Fleets](https://memclaw.net/blog/memclaw-benchmarks) (2026-04-19).\n294: \n295: ---\n296: \n297: ## MCP (Model Context Protocol)\n298: \n299: Add MemClaw to any MCP client with one config block.\n300: \n301: **Self-hosted** (localhost):\n302: \n303: ```json\n304: {\n305:   \"mcpServers\": {\n306:     \"memclaw\": {\n307:       \"url\": \"http://localhost:8000/mcp\",\n308:       \"headers\": { \"X-API-Key\": \"standalone\" }\n309:     }\n310:   }\n311: }\n312: ```\n313: \n314: **Managed platform** (memclaw.net):\n315: \n316: ```json\n317: {\n318:   \"mcpServers\": {\n319:     \"memclaw\": {\n320:       \"url\": \"https://memclaw.net/mcp\",\n321:       \"headers\": { \"X-API-Key\": \"mc_your_api_key_here\" }\n322:     }\n323:   }\n324: }\n325: ```\n326: \n327: > For team or production use, swap the tenant-scoped key for an **agent-scoped credential** — atomic provisioning via `POST /api/v1/admin/agent-keys/provision` (or the `/settings/organization/api-credentials` wizard) mints the credential + Agent row + initial trust + fleet membership in one round trip. Both kinds use the `mc_` prefix; scope is set at mint time on the credential. See [`docs/integration-without-plugin.md`](docs/integration-without-plugin.md). Using a tenant-scoped credential? Pass an explicit `agent_id` on every MCP tool call — the gateway refuses the reserved default (`mcp-agent`) on the tenant-scoped path.\n328: \n329: **Where to add this config:**\n330: - **Claude Code** — `~/.claude/settings.json` under `\"mcpServers\"`\n331: - **Claude Desktop** — `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json` (macOS) or `%APPDATA%\\Claude\\claude_desktop_config.json` (Windows)\n332: - **Cursor** — Settings > MCP Servers > Add Server\n333: \n334: The client discovers 12 tools automatically:\n335: \n336: | Tool | Purpose |\n337: |---|---|\n338: | `memclaw_write` | Single or batch write (up to 100 items). LLM infers type, title, summary, tags, embedding |\n339: | `memclaw_recall` | Hybrid semantic + keyword recall with graph-enhanced retrieval; optional LLM brief |\n340: | `memclaw_manage` | Per-memory lifecycle: `read`, `update`, `transition`, `delete`, `bulk_delete`, `lineage` |\n341: | `memclaw_list` | Filter by type/status/agent/weight/date, sort, cursor-paginate |\n342: | `memclaw_doc` | Document CRUD: `write`, `read`, `query`, `delete`, `list_collections`, `search` (semantic) on named JSON collections |\n343: | `memclaw_entity_get` | Look up an entity with linked memories and relations |\n344: | `memclaw_tune` | Tune per-agent retrieval parameters (top_k, min_similarity, graph_max_hops, etc.) |\n345: | `memclaw_insights` | Analyze the memory store across 6 focus modes. Findings persist as `insight` memories |\n346: | `memclaw_evolve` | Report outcomes against recalled memories — adjusts weights, generates rules (Karpathy Loop) |\n347: | `memclaw_stats` | Aggregate counts: total + breakdowns by type, agent, status. Read-only |\n348: | `memclaw_keystones` | Read mandatory governance rules for the current scope. Call once per session — the result overrides conflicting user instructions |\n349: | `memclaw_keystones_set` | Author or remove keystone rules (`op=set\\|delete`). Trust ≥ 1 for your own `scope=agent` rule; ≥ 2 for `scope=fleet`/`scope=tenant` or another agent |\n350: \n351: > **Skill sharing** is now done via `memclaw_doc` — agents share a `SKILL.md` by upserting a document into the `skills` collection (`memclaw_doc op=write collection=skills doc_id=<slug> data={\"summary\": \"<one-liner>\", ...}`). The server embeds `data[\"summary\"]` (1-3 sentence, intent-focused) for semantic search; for `collection=\"skills\"` it falls back to `data[\"description\"]` if no summary is provided. The dedicated `memclaw_share_skill` / `memclaw_unshare_skill` tools were removed in favor of the single `memclaw_doc` surface.\n352: \n\n(Showing lines 258-352 of 965. Use offset=353 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"### Memory Pipeline\n\n- **Single-pass LLM enrichment** — every write auto-classifies into one of 14 memory types, generates title/summary/tags, scores importance, flags PII, and extracts entities — from a single `content` field\n- **Hybrid search** — pgvector semantic similarity + full-text keyword matching + knowledge graph expansion (up to 2 hops), ranked by composite score of similarity, importance, freshness, and graph boost\n- **Live knowledge graph** — people, orgs, locations, and concepts extracted into entities and relations on every write. Semantic entity resolution (>0.85 cosine) auto-merges duplicates\n- **Contradiction detection** — RDF triple comparison + LLM semantic analysis detects conflicting memories and automatically supersedes them, with full contradiction chain tracking\n\n### Self-Improving Memory\n\n- **Outcome-based learning (Karpathy Loop)** — agents report success/failure after acting on recalled memories; the system reinforces what works and auto-generates preventive `rule`-type memories on failure\n- **Crystallization** — LLM merges near-duplicate memories into canonical atomic facts with full provenance; 8-status lifecycle automation retires stale data\n- **Per-agent retrieval tuning** — each agent optimizes its own retrieval profile (top_k, min_similarity, graph_max_hops, blend weights) from feedback, so search quality compounds with every interaction\n\n### Integrations\n\n- **MCP server** — built-in [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io) at `/mcp` (Streamable HTTP). Connect Claude Desktop, Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, or any MCP client with a URL and API key\n- **Multi-provider LLM** — primary + fallback provider chain per tenant (OpenAI, Gemini, Anthropic, OpenRouter) with platform defaults for zero-config tenants\n- **Document store** — structured JSONB collections alongside semantic memories for exact-field lookups (customer records, config, task lists)\n\n---","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","text":"### Memory Pipeline\n\n- **Single-pass LLM enrichment** — every write auto-classifies into one of 14 memory types, generates title/summary/tags, scores importance, flags PII, and extracts entities — from a single `content` field\n- **Hybrid search** — pgvector semantic similarity + full-text keyword matching + knowledge graph expansion (up to 2 hops), ranked by composite score of similarity, importance, freshness, and graph boost\n- **Live knowledge graph** — people, orgs, locations, and concepts extracted into entities and relations on every write. Semantic entity resolution (>0.85 cosine) auto-merges duplicates\n- **Contradiction detection** — RDF triple comparison + LLM semantic analysis detects conflicting memories and automatically supersedes them, with full contradiction chain tracking\n\n### Self-Improving Memory\n\n- **Outcome-based learning (Karpathy Loop)** — agents report success/failure after acting on recalled memories; the system reinforces what works and auto-generates preventive `rule`-type memories on failure\n- **Crystallization** — LLM merges near-duplicate memories into canonical atomic facts with full provenance; 8-status lifecycle automation retires stale data\n- **Per-agent retrieval tuning** — each agent optimizes its own retrieval profile (top_k, min_similarity, graph_max_hops, blend weights) from feedback, so search quality compounds with every interaction\n\n### Integrations\n\n- **MCP server** — built-in [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io) at `/mcp` (Streamable HTTP). Connect Claude Desktop, Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, or any MCP client with a URL and API key\n- **Multi-provider LLM** — primary + fallback provider chain per tenant (OpenAI, Gemini, Anthropic, OpenRouter) with platform defaults for zero-config tenants\n- **Document store** — structured JSONB collections alongside semantic memories for exact-field lookups (customer records, config, task lists)\n\n---\n\n## Performance\n\nBenchmarked against the two most-cited public agent-memory benchmarks. Methodology and operator-scale context live in [`docs/performance.md`](docs/performance.md); the full write-up is on the blog.\n\n|  | LoCoMo | LongMemEval | Search latency |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Accuracy (LLM-judge) | **77.6%** | **72.5%** | — |\n| Token savings vs full context | **96.6%** | **98.2%** | — |\n| Latency | — | — | **23 ms p50 · 27 ms p95** |\n\nAccuracy sits inside the leading cluster across the field (Mem0, Zep, MemClaw — scores cluster in a narrow band). The axes we push hardest are latency and token efficiency, because those are the ones that compound as agent count grows — a few hundred ms of search latency disappears behind one LLM call, but bills millions of times a day across a fleet.\n\n> Single-agent benchmarks can't measure cross-agent recall, outcome propagation between agents, fleet-scoped visibility, or governance-aware retrieval. Those are the questions that decide whether a memory system is *deployable* inside a company. See [`docs/performance.md`](docs/performance.md#what-these-benchmarks-cant-measure).\n\nSource: [Fast, Token-Efficient, and Built for Fleets](https://memclaw.net/blog/memclaw-benchmarks) (2026-04-19).\n\n---\n\n## MCP (Model Context Protocol)\n\nAdd MemClaw to any MCP client with one config block.\n\n**Self-hosted** (localhost):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"memclaw\": {\n      \"url\": \"http://localhost:8000/mcp\",\n      \"headers\": { \"X-API-Key\": \"standalone\" }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Managed platform** (memclaw.net):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"memclaw\": {\n      \"url\": \"https://memclaw.net/mcp\",\n      \"headers\": { \"X-API-Key\": \"mc_your_api_key_here\" }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n> For team or production use, swap the tenant-scoped key for an **agent-scoped credential** — atomic provisioning via `POST /api/v1/admin/agent-keys/provision` (or the `/settings/organization/api-credentials` wizard) mints the credential + Agent row + initial trust + fleet membership in one round trip. Both kinds use the `mc_` prefix; scope is set at mint time on the credential. See [`docs/integration-without-plugin.md`](docs/integration-without-plugin.md). Using a tenant-scoped credential? Pass an explicit `agent_id` on every MCP tool call — the gateway refuses the reserved default (`mcp-agent`) on the tenant-scoped path.\n\n**Where to add this config:**\n- **Claude Code** — `~/.claude/settings.json` under `\"mcpServers\"`\n- **Claude Desktop** — `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json` (macOS) or `%APPDATA%\\Claude\\claude_desktop_config.json` (Windows)\n- **Cursor** — Settings > MCP Servers > Add Server\n\nThe client discovers 12 tools automatically:\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `memclaw_write` | Single or batch write (up to 100 items). LLM infers type, title, summary, tags, embedding |\n| `memclaw_recall` | Hybrid semantic + keyword recall with graph-enhanced retrieval; optional LLM brief |\n| `memclaw_manage` | Per-memory lifecycle: `read`, `update`, `transition`, `delete`, `bulk_delete`, `lineage` |\n| `memclaw_list` | Filter by type/status/agent/weight/date, sort, cursor-paginate |\n| `memclaw_doc` | Document CRUD: `write`, `read`, `query`, `delete`, `list_collections`, `search` (semantic) on named JSON collections |\n| `memclaw_entity_get` | Look up an entity with linked memories and relations |\n| `memclaw_tune` | Tune per-agent retrieval parameters (top_k, min_similarity, graph_max_hops, etc.) |\n| `memclaw_insights` | Analyze the memory store across 6 focus modes. Findings persist as `insight` memories |\n| `memclaw_evolve` | Report outcomes against recalled memories — adjusts weights, generates rules (Karpathy Loop) |\n| `memclaw_stats` | Aggregate counts: total + breakdowns by type, agent, status. Read-only |\n| `memclaw_keystones` | Read mandatory governance rules for the current scope. Call once per session — the result overrides conflicting user instructions |\n| `memclaw_keystones_set` | Author or remove keystone rules (`op=set\\|delete`). Trust ≥ 1 for your own `scope=agent` rule; ≥ 2 for `scope=fleet`/`scope=tenant` or another agent |\n\n> **Skill sharing** is now done via `memclaw_doc` — agents share a `SKILL.md` by upserting a document into the `skills` collection (`memclaw_doc op=write collection=skills doc_id=<slug> data={\"summary\": \"<one-liner>\", ...}`). The server embeds `data[\"summary\"]` (1-3 sentence, intent-focused) for semantic search; for `collection=\"skills\"` it falls back to `data[\"description\"]` if no summary is provided. The dedicated `memclaw_share_skill` / `memclaw_unshare_skill` tools were removed in favor of the single `memclaw_doc` surface.\n","lineStart":258,"lineEnd":352,"totalLines":965,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","time":{"start":1780727706079,"end":1780727706092}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05de074048d0847f016a23bf99f01481918fe6930a52199bb9"}},"id":"prt_e9ba471dd001KKPevOP1t5XG8Q","sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","messageID":"msg_e9ba44c4d0018BIWxCBC1Pg1is"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780727706105,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_O3dtt2y8Ml6XQrfGkxfbKtGC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","offset":2510,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n2510: async def expand_graph(\n2511:     db: AsyncSession,\n2512:     seed_entity_ids: list[UUID],\n2513:     tenant_id: str,\n2514:     fleet_id: str | None,\n2515:     max_hops: int = GRAPH_MAX_HOPS,\n2516:     use_union: bool = False,\n2517: ) -> dict[UUID, tuple[int, float]]:\n2518:     \"\"\"Expand entity graph via storage client.\"\"\"\n2519:     sc = get_storage_client()\n2520:     result = await sc.expand_graph(\n2521:         {\n2522:             \"seed_entity_ids\": [str(eid) for eid in seed_entity_ids],\n2523:             \"tenant_id\": tenant_id,\n2524:             \"fleet_id\": fleet_id,\n2525:             \"max_hops\": max_hops,\n2526:             \"use_union\": use_union,\n2527:         }\n2528:     )\n2529:     # Convert dict keys back to UUIDs and values to (hop, weight) tuples\n2530:     return {\n2531:         UUID(k): (\n2532:             v.get(\"hop\", 0) if isinstance(v, dict) else v[0],\n2533:             v.get(\"weight\", 1.0) if isinstance(v, dict) else v[1],\n2534:         )\n2535:         for k, v in result.items()\n2536:     }\n2537: \n2538: \n2539: def _is_specific_token(token: str) -> bool:\n2540:     \"\"\"Check if a token looks like a proper noun, identifier, or ticker.\"\"\"\n2541:     if not token:\n2542:         return False\n2543:     # All-caps acronym (NEXAI, BTC, GPT) or CamelCase/PascalCase (CertiK, OpenAI)\n2544:     if token.isupper() or (token[0].isupper() and any(c.isupper() for c in token[1:])):\n2545:         return True\n2546:     # Contains digits (IDs, versions, codes): \"gpt-5\", \"1892347\"\n2547:     if any(c.isdigit() for c in token):\n2548:         return True\n2549:     # Starts with special chars (tickers, handles): \"$SOL\", \"@karpathy\", \"#trending\"\n2550:     if token[0] in (\"$\", \"@\", \"#\"):\n2551:         return True\n2552:     return False\n2553: \n2554: \n2555: def _adaptive_fts_weight(query: str) -> float:\n2556:     \"\"\"Return a boosted FTS weight for short, specific queries.\n2557: \n2558:     A27 — shares the canonical tokenizer with the entity-FTS gate so a\n2559:     hyphenated query like ``claude-opus-4-7`` no longer produces a\n2560:     1-token view here but a 4-token view at ``extract_entity_tokens``.\n2561:     Two behavioural details are preserved across the share:\n2562: \n2563:     1. ``MAX_TOKENS`` gates on RAW whitespace count, not on the\n2564:        post-filter token count. A 4+ word natural-language sentence\n2565:        should stay default-weight even when the shared filter would\n2566:        collapse it to a single meaningful token (``\"tell me about\n2567:        NEXAI\"`` → semantic-heavy, don't boost).\n2568:     2. Sigil tokens (``$BTC`` / ``@karpathy`` / ``#trending``) are\n2569:        detected on the RAW query before ``extract_entity_tokens``\n2570:        strips leading punctuation, so the handle / ticker / hashtag\n2571:        signal that ``_is_specific_token`` keys on still fires after\n2572:        the share.\n2573:     \"\"\"\n2574:     from core_api.services.entity_tokens import extract_entity_tokens\n2575: \n2576:     raw = query.split()\n2577:     if len(raw) > FTS_BOOST_MAX_TOKENS:\n2578:         return FTS_WEIGHT\n2579: \n2580:     tokens = extract_entity_tokens(query, preserve_case=True)\n2581:     sigil_count = sum(1 for t in raw if t and t[0] in (\"$\", \"@\", \"#\") and len(t) > 1)\n2582: \n2583:     if not tokens and sigil_count == 0:\n2584:         return FTS_WEIGHT\n2585: \n2586:     specific_count = sum(1 for t in tokens if _is_specific_token(t)) + sigil_count\n2587:     denom = len(tokens) or 1\n2588:     if specific_count / denom > FTS_BOOST_SPECIFICITY_RATIO:\n2589:         return FTS_WEIGHT_BOOSTED\n2590: \n2591:     return FTS_WEIGHT\n2592: \n2593: \n2594: def _normalize_query_for_cache(query: str) -> str:\n2595:     \"\"\"Normalize query for cache key: lowercase, strip, collapse whitespace.\"\"\"\n2596:     return re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", query.strip().lower())\n2597: \n2598: \n2599: # Per-process stampede guard for cold-cache embed calls. Maps cache-key to\n2600: # the in-flight Future producing the embedding. When N concurrent callers\n2601: # miss the cache for the same key, the first arrival registers the Future\n2602: # and fires the embed call; subsequent arrivals find the Future and await\n2603: # its result instead of each issuing their own OpenAI round-trip.\n2604: #\n2605: # Scope is intentionally per-process: a Redis-side lock would coordinate\n2606: # across replicas but the latency floor of the read path is already a\n2607: # single embed call per cold key per replica, and the stampede pattern\n2608: # observed in production is dominated by the same client issuing N\n2609: # parallel recalls (e.g. fan-out probe, agent batch) hitting the same\n2610: # replica. Cache_set still happens, so once any replica completes the\n2611: # embed, the next request — local OR remote — finds it in Redis.\n2612: _inflight_embeddings: dict[str, asyncio.Future] = {}\n2613: \n2614: \n2615: async def _get_or_cache_embedding(query: str, tenant_id: str, tenant_config):\n2616:     \"\"\"Get embedding from cache or generate it.\n2617: \n2618:     The cache key includes ``VECTOR_DIM`` so that a schema-dimension\n2619:     migration doesn't surface stale cached embeddings to the new schema;\n2620:     old entries with a mismatched dim become unreachable under the new\n2621:     key and expire naturally via ``EMBEDDING_CACHE_TTL``.\n2622: \n2623:     The cache key also includes ``EMBEDDING_QUERY_INSTRUCTION`` (C9):\n2624:     instruction-aware models (Qwen3-Embedding, e5-instruct, KaLM) prepend\n2625:     the resolved instruction to the query before encoding, so the SAME\n2626:     raw query under TWO different instructions produces TWO different\n2627:     embeddings. Omitting the instruction from the key meant an env-var\n2628:     change (or set / unset) served stale embeddings until the TTL\n2629:     expired. The registry-level provider cache already keys on this —\n2630:     we mirror it at the search-cache layer.\n2631: \n2632:     Concurrent cold-cache callers for the same key share a single\n2633:     ``get_query_embedding`` round-trip via ``_inflight_embeddings`` —\n2634:     measured 3-second tail spread on 5 parallel novel-query recalls\n2635:     pre-fix; post-fix all callers join the leader's future.\n2636:     \"\"\"\n2637:     import os\n2638: \n2639:     from core_api.cache import cache_get, cache_set\n2640: \n2641:     _model = (\n2642:         getattr(tenant_config, \"embedding_model\", None) if tenant_config is not None else None\n2643:     ) or OPENAI_EMBEDDING_MODEL\n2644:     _normalized = _normalize_query_for_cache(query)\n2645:     # Resolved instruction — same env var the OpenAI provider reads at\n2646:     # registry-construction time (common/embedding/_registry.py:218). When\n2647:     # unset, we hash the empty string so the key stays stable across\n2648:     # never-set vs explicitly-empty (both behave identically downstream:\n2649:     # the provider's ``embed_query`` short-circuits the instruction\n2650:     # prefix).\n2651:     _instruction = os.environ.get(\"EMBEDDING_QUERY_INSTRUCTION\") or \"\"\n2652:     _qhash = hashlib.sha256(\n2653:         f\"{_model}:{VECTOR_DIM}:{_instruction}:{tenant_id}:{_normalized}\".encode()\n2654:     ).hexdigest()\n2655:     # Prefix bumped from ``qemb3:`` → ``qemb4:`` because the hash input\n2656:     # changed (added ``EMBEDDING_QUERY_INSTRUCTION``). The bump makes the\n2657:     # cache-generation boundary explicit in Redis key stats so an\n2658:     # operator can see the cold-start at deploy time and confirm the\n2659:     # embedding provider can absorb the working-set re-fetch. Old\n2660:     # ``qemb3:*`` entries expire naturally via ``EMBEDDING_CACHE_TTL``.\n2661:     _cache_key = f\"qemb4:{_qhash}\"\n2662:     _cached_raw = await cache_get(_cache_key)\n2663:     if _cached_raw is not None:\n2664:         try:\n2665:             return json.loads(_cached_raw)\n2666:         except (ValueError, TypeError):\n2667:             pass\n2668: \n2669:     # Cold cache: check whether another coroutine is already producing\n2670:     # this embedding. If so, await its result. Otherwise become the\n2671:     # leader, register the future, and fire the embed call.\n2672:     inflight = _inflight_embeddings.get(_cache_key)\n2673:     if inflight is not None:\n2674:         return await inflight\n2675: \n2676:     loop = asyncio.get_running_loop()\n2677:     fut: asyncio.Future = loop.create_future()\n2678:     _inflight_embeddings[_cache_key] = fut\n2679:     try:\n2680:         # Search-side embed uses the instruction-aware path. For symmetric\n2681:         # models (OpenAI, bge, snowflake-m, gte-en-v1.5) this is identical to\n2682:         # ``get_embedding(query, tenant_config)``. For instruction-aware models\n2683:         # (Qwen3-Embedding, e5-instruct), the provider prepends the configured\n2684:         # task instruction (env: ``EMBEDDING_QUERY_INSTRUCTION``) so the query\n2685:         # is encoded with the same instruction prefix the model was trained on.\n2686:         # Documents (writes) embed unmodified text.\n2687:         embedding = await asyncio.wait_for(get_query_embedding(query, tenant_config), timeout=10.0)\n2688:         if embedding is None:\n2689:             raise ValueError(\"Embedding service unavailable\")\n2690:         await cache_set(_cache_key, json.dumps(embedding), ttl=EMBEDDING_CACHE_TTL)\n2691:         fut.set_result(embedding)\n2692:         return embedding\n2693:     except BaseException as exc:\n2694:         # Propagate to every waiter so they raise consistently rather\n2695:         # than hanging forever on a fulfilled-never future. BaseException\n2696:         # catches CancelledError too — leaking a cancelled future would\n2697:         # otherwise strand every joiner. The leader re-raises after the\n2698:         # finally block.\n2699:         if not fut.done():\n2700:             fut.set_exception(exc)\n2701:         raise\n2702:     finally:\n2703:         # Drop the inflight slot only after the future has been resolved.\n2704:         # A late arrival that read the slot before this pop still gets\n2705:         # the cached future and awaits its already-resolved state.\n2706:         _inflight_embeddings.pop(_cache_key, None)\n2707: \n2708: \n2709: async def _entity_boost_pipeline(\n2710:     db: AsyncSession,\n2711:     query: str,\n2712:     tenant_id: str,\n2713:     fleet_ids: list[str] | None,\n2714:     graph_expand: bool,\n2715:     graph_max_hops: int,\n2716:     use_union: bool = False,\n2717:     precomputed_hops: dict[UUID, tuple[int, float]] | None = None,\n2718: ) -> tuple[set[UUID], dict[UUID, float]]:\n2719:     \"\"\"Run entity FTS matching -> graph expansion -> link collection.\n2720: \n2721:     Returns (boosted_memory_ids, memory_boost_factor).\n2722:     Independent of embedding -- can run in parallel.\n2723: \n2724:     When *precomputed_hops* is supplied (from ClassifyQuery fallthrough),\n2725:     entity FTS and graph expansion are skipped to avoid double DB roundtrips.\n2726:     \"\"\"\n2727:     sc = get_storage_client()\n2728:     boosted_memory_ids: set[UUID] = set()\n2729:     memory_boost_factor: dict[UUID, float] = {}\n2730: \n2731:     try:\n2732:         if precomputed_hops is not None:\n2733:             entity_hops = precomputed_hops\n2734:             matched_entity_ids = [eid for eid, (hop, _w) in entity_hops.items() if hop == 0]\n2735:         else:\n2736:             tokens = extract_entity_tokens(query)\n2737:             if not tokens:\n2738:                 return boosted_memory_ids, memory_boost_factor\n2739: \n2740:             # Entity FTS search via storage client\n2741:             matched_entity_ids_raw = await sc.fts_search_entities(\n2742:                 {\n2743:                     \"tenant_id\": tenant_id,\n2744:                     \"tokens\": tokens,\n2745:                     \"fleet_ids\": fleet_ids,\n2746:                 }\n2747:             )\n2748:             matched_entity_ids = [UUID(eid) for eid in matched_entity_ids_raw]\n2749: \n2750:             if not matched_entity_ids:\n2751:                 return boosted_memory_ids, memory_boost_factor\n2752: \n2753:             # Graph expansion\n2754:             if graph_expand and graph_max_hops > 0:\n2755:                 entity_hops = await expand_graph(\n2756:                     db,\n2757:                     matched_entity_ids,\n2758:                     tenant_id,\n2759:                     fleet_ids[0] if fleet_ids and len(fleet_ids) == 1 else None,\n2760:                     max_hops=graph_max_hops,\n2761:                     use_union=use_union,\n2762:                 )\n2763:             else:\n2764:                 entity_hops = dict.fromkeys(matched_entity_ids, (0, 1.0))\n2765: \n2766:         if matched_entity_ids:\n2767:             # Collect memories linked to discovered entities via storage client\n2768:             all_entity_ids = list(entity_hops.keys())\n2769:             all_links_raw = await sc.get_memory_ids_by_entity_ids([str(eid) for eid in all_entity_ids])\n\n(Showing lines 2510-2769 of 3230. Use offset=2770 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"async def expand_graph(\n    db: AsyncSession,\n    seed_entity_ids: list[UUID],\n    tenant_id: str,\n    fleet_id: str | None,\n    max_hops: int = GRAPH_MAX_HOPS,\n    use_union: bool = False,\n) -> dict[UUID, tuple[int, float]]:\n    \"\"\"Expand entity graph via storage client.\"\"\"\n    sc = get_storage_client()\n    result = await sc.expand_graph(\n        {\n            \"seed_entity_ids\": [str(eid) for eid in seed_entity_ids],\n            \"tenant_id\": tenant_id,\n            \"fleet_id\": fleet_id,\n            \"max_hops\": max_hops,\n            \"use_union\": use_union,\n        }\n    )\n    # Convert dict keys back to UUIDs and values to (hop, weight) tuples","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","text":"async def expand_graph(\n    db: AsyncSession,\n    seed_entity_ids: list[UUID],\n    tenant_id: str,\n    fleet_id: str | None,\n    max_hops: int = GRAPH_MAX_HOPS,\n    use_union: bool = False,\n) -> dict[UUID, tuple[int, float]]:\n    \"\"\"Expand entity graph via storage client.\"\"\"\n    sc = get_storage_client()\n    result = await sc.expand_graph(\n        {\n            \"seed_entity_ids\": [str(eid) for eid in seed_entity_ids],\n            \"tenant_id\": tenant_id,\n            \"fleet_id\": fleet_id,\n            \"max_hops\": max_hops,\n            \"use_union\": use_union,\n        }\n    )\n    # Convert dict keys back to UUIDs and values to (hop, weight) tuples\n    return {\n        UUID(k): (\n            v.get(\"hop\", 0) if isinstance(v, dict) else v[0],\n            v.get(\"weight\", 1.0) if isinstance(v, dict) else v[1],\n        )\n        for k, v in result.items()\n    }\n\n\ndef _is_specific_token(token: str) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Check if a token looks like a proper noun, identifier, or ticker.\"\"\"\n    if not token:\n        return False\n    # All-caps acronym (NEXAI, BTC, GPT) or CamelCase/PascalCase (CertiK, OpenAI)\n    if token.isupper() or (token[0].isupper() and any(c.isupper() for c in token[1:])):\n        return True\n    # Contains digits (IDs, versions, codes): \"gpt-5\", \"1892347\"\n    if any(c.isdigit() for c in token):\n        return True\n    # Starts with special chars (tickers, handles): \"$SOL\", \"@karpathy\", \"#trending\"\n    if token[0] in (\"$\", \"@\", \"#\"):\n        return True\n    return False\n\n\ndef _adaptive_fts_weight(query: str) -> float:\n    \"\"\"Return a boosted FTS weight for short, specific queries.\n\n    A27 — shares the canonical tokenizer with the entity-FTS gate so a\n    hyphenated query like ``claude-opus-4-7`` no longer produces a\n    1-token view here but a 4-token view at ``extract_entity_tokens``.\n    Two behavioural details are preserved across the share:\n\n    1. ``MAX_TOKENS`` gates on RAW whitespace count, not on the\n       post-filter token count. A 4+ word natural-language sentence\n       should stay default-weight even when the shared filter would\n       collapse it to a single meaningful token (``\"tell me about\n       NEXAI\"`` → semantic-heavy, don't boost).\n    2. Sigil tokens (``$BTC`` / ``@karpathy`` / ``#trending``) are\n       detected on the RAW query before ``extract_entity_tokens``\n       strips leading punctuation, so the handle / ticker / hashtag\n       signal that ``_is_specific_token`` keys on still fires after\n       the share.\n    \"\"\"\n    from core_api.services.entity_tokens import extract_entity_tokens\n\n    raw = query.split()\n    if len(raw) > FTS_BOOST_MAX_TOKENS:\n        return FTS_WEIGHT\n\n    tokens = extract_entity_tokens(query, preserve_case=True)\n    sigil_count = sum(1 for t in raw if t and t[0] in (\"$\", \"@\", \"#\") and len(t) > 1)\n\n    if not tokens and sigil_count == 0:\n        return FTS_WEIGHT\n\n    specific_count = sum(1 for t in tokens if _is_specific_token(t)) + sigil_count\n    denom = len(tokens) or 1\n    if specific_count / denom > FTS_BOOST_SPECIFICITY_RATIO:\n        return FTS_WEIGHT_BOOSTED\n\n    return FTS_WEIGHT\n\n\ndef _normalize_query_for_cache(query: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Normalize query for cache key: lowercase, strip, collapse whitespace.\"\"\"\n    return re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", query.strip().lower())\n\n\n# Per-process stampede guard for cold-cache embed calls. Maps cache-key to\n# the in-flight Future producing the embedding. When N concurrent callers\n# miss the cache for the same key, the first arrival registers the Future\n# and fires the embed call; subsequent arrivals find the Future and await\n# its result instead of each issuing their own OpenAI round-trip.\n#\n# Scope is intentionally per-process: a Redis-side lock would coordinate\n# across replicas but the latency floor of the read path is already a\n# single embed call per cold key per replica, and the stampede pattern\n# observed in production is dominated by the same client issuing N\n# parallel recalls (e.g. fan-out probe, agent batch) hitting the same\n# replica. Cache_set still happens, so once any replica completes the\n# embed, the next request — local OR remote — finds it in Redis.\n_inflight_embeddings: dict[str, asyncio.Future] = {}\n\n\nasync def _get_or_cache_embedding(query: str, tenant_id: str, tenant_config):\n    \"\"\"Get embedding from cache or generate it.\n\n    The cache key includes ``VECTOR_DIM`` so that a schema-dimension\n    migration doesn't surface stale cached embeddings to the new schema;\n    old entries with a mismatched dim become unreachable under the new\n    key and expire naturally via ``EMBEDDING_CACHE_TTL``.\n\n    The cache key also includes ``EMBEDDING_QUERY_INSTRUCTION`` (C9):\n    instruction-aware models (Qwen3-Embedding, e5-instruct, KaLM) prepend\n    the resolved instruction to the query before encoding, so the SAME\n    raw query under TWO different instructions produces TWO different\n    embeddings. Omitting the instruction from the key meant an env-var\n    change (or set / unset) served stale embeddings until the TTL\n    expired. The registry-level provider cache already keys on this —\n    we mirror it at the search-cache layer.\n\n    Concurrent cold-cache callers for the same key share a single\n    ``get_query_embedding`` round-trip via ``_inflight_embeddings`` —\n    measured 3-second tail spread on 5 parallel novel-query recalls\n    pre-fix; post-fix all callers join the leader's future.\n    \"\"\"\n    import os\n\n    from core_api.cache import cache_get, cache_set\n\n    _model = (\n        getattr(tenant_config, \"embedding_model\", None) if tenant_config is not None else None\n    ) or OPENAI_EMBEDDING_MODEL\n    _normalized = _normalize_query_for_cache(query)\n    # Resolved instruction — same env var the OpenAI provider reads at\n    # registry-construction time (common/embedding/_registry.py:218). When\n    # unset, we hash the empty string so the key stays stable across\n    # never-set vs explicitly-empty (both behave identically downstream:\n    # the provider's ``embed_query`` short-circuits the instruction\n    # prefix).\n    _instruction = os.environ.get(\"EMBEDDING_QUERY_INSTRUCTION\") or \"\"\n    _qhash = hashlib.sha256(\n        f\"{_model}:{VECTOR_DIM}:{_instruction}:{tenant_id}:{_normalized}\".encode()\n    ).hexdigest()\n    # Prefix bumped from ``qemb3:`` → ``qemb4:`` because the hash input\n    # changed (added ``EMBEDDING_QUERY_INSTRUCTION``). The bump makes the\n    # cache-generation boundary explicit in Redis key stats so an\n    # operator can see the cold-start at deploy time and confirm the\n    # embedding provider can absorb the working-set re-fetch. Old\n    # ``qemb3:*`` entries expire naturally via ``EMBEDDING_CACHE_TTL``.\n    _cache_key = f\"qemb4:{_qhash}\"\n    _cached_raw = await cache_get(_cache_key)\n    if _cached_raw is not None:\n        try:\n            return json.loads(_cached_raw)\n        except (ValueError, TypeError):\n            pass\n\n    # Cold cache: check whether another coroutine is already producing\n    # this embedding. If so, await its result. Otherwise become the\n    # leader, register the future, and fire the embed call.\n    inflight = _inflight_embeddings.get(_cache_key)\n    if inflight is not None:\n        return await inflight\n\n    loop = asyncio.get_running_loop()\n    fut: asyncio.Future = loop.create_future()\n    _inflight_embeddings[_cache_key] = fut\n    try:\n        # Search-side embed uses the instruction-aware path. For symmetric\n        # models (OpenAI, bge, snowflake-m, gte-en-v1.5) this is identical to\n        # ``get_embedding(query, tenant_config)``. For instruction-aware models\n        # (Qwen3-Embedding, e5-instruct), the provider prepends the configured\n        # task instruction (env: ``EMBEDDING_QUERY_INSTRUCTION``) so the query\n        # is encoded with the same instruction prefix the model was trained on.\n        # Documents (writes) embed unmodified text.\n        embedding = await asyncio.wait_for(get_query_embedding(query, tenant_config), timeout=10.0)\n        if embedding is None:\n            raise ValueError(\"Embedding service unavailable\")\n        await cache_set(_cache_key, json.dumps(embedding), ttl=EMBEDDING_CACHE_TTL)\n        fut.set_result(embedding)\n        return embedding\n    except BaseException as exc:\n        # Propagate to every waiter so they raise consistently rather\n        # than hanging forever on a fulfilled-never future. BaseException\n        # catches CancelledError too — leaking a cancelled future would\n        # otherwise strand every joiner. The leader re-raises after the\n        # finally block.\n        if not fut.done():\n            fut.set_exception(exc)\n        raise\n    finally:\n        # Drop the inflight slot only after the future has been resolved.\n        # A late arrival that read the slot before this pop still gets\n        # the cached future and awaits its already-resolved state.\n        _inflight_embeddings.pop(_cache_key, None)\n\n\nasync def _entity_boost_pipeline(\n    db: AsyncSession,\n    query: str,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    fleet_ids: list[str] | None,\n    graph_expand: bool,\n    graph_max_hops: int,\n    use_union: bool = False,\n    precomputed_hops: dict[UUID, tuple[int, float]] | None = None,\n) -> tuple[set[UUID], dict[UUID, float]]:\n    \"\"\"Run entity FTS matching -> graph expansion -> link collection.\n\n    Returns (boosted_memory_ids, memory_boost_factor).\n    Independent of embedding -- can run in parallel.\n\n    When *precomputed_hops* is supplied (from ClassifyQuery fallthrough),\n    entity FTS and graph expansion are skipped to avoid double DB roundtrips.\n    \"\"\"\n    sc = get_storage_client()\n    boosted_memory_ids: set[UUID] = set()\n    memory_boost_factor: dict[UUID, float] = {}\n\n    try:\n        if precomputed_hops is not None:\n            entity_hops = precomputed_hops\n            matched_entity_ids = [eid for eid, (hop, _w) in entity_hops.items() if hop == 0]\n        else:\n            tokens = extract_entity_tokens(query)\n            if not tokens:\n                return boosted_memory_ids, memory_boost_factor\n\n            # Entity FTS search via storage client\n            matched_entity_ids_raw = await sc.fts_search_entities(\n                {\n                    \"tenant_id\": tenant_id,\n                    \"tokens\": tokens,\n                    \"fleet_ids\": fleet_ids,\n                }\n            )\n            matched_entity_ids = [UUID(eid) for eid in matched_entity_ids_raw]\n\n            if not matched_entity_ids:\n                return boosted_memory_ids, memory_boost_factor\n\n            # Graph expansion\n            if graph_expand and graph_max_hops > 0:\n                entity_hops = await expand_graph(\n                    db,\n                    matched_entity_ids,\n                    tenant_id,\n                    fleet_ids[0] if fleet_ids and len(fleet_ids) == 1 else None,\n                    max_hops=graph_max_hops,\n                    use_union=use_union,\n                )\n            else:\n                entity_hops = dict.fromkeys(matched_entity_ids, (0, 1.0))\n\n        if matched_entity_ids:\n            # Collect memories linked to discovered entities via storage client\n            all_entity_ids = list(entity_hops.keys())\n            all_links_raw = await sc.get_memory_ids_by_entity_ids([str(eid) for eid in all_entity_ids])","lineStart":2510,"lineEnd":2769,"totalLines":3230,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","time":{"start":1780727706064,"end":1780727706102}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05de074048d0847f016a23bf99efe88191bf3bffa5942c1337"}},"id":"prt_e9ba47192001sLtJa6d0I3I62L","sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","messageID":"msg_e9ba44c4d0018BIWxCBC1Pg1is"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780727706109,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_GEbvurtcoEwKvCI9jyOxPH2P","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","offset":2960,"limit":280},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n2960:         return {\"start_date\": start.isoformat(), \"end_date\": end.isoformat()}\n2961: \n2962:     return None\n2963: \n2964: \n2965: async def search_memories(\n2966:     db: AsyncSession,\n2967:     tenant_id: str,\n2968:     query: str,\n2969:     fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n2970:     filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n2971:     caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n2972:     memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n2973:     status_filter: str | None = None,\n2974:     valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n2975:     top_k: int = DEFAULT_SEARCH_TOP_K,\n2976:     recall_boost: bool = True,\n2977:     graph_expand: bool = True,\n2978:     tenant_config=None,\n2979:     search_profile: dict | None = None,\n2980:     diagnostic: bool = False,\n2981:     diagnostic_ctx: dict | None = None,\n2982:     readable_tenant_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n2983: ) -> list[MemoryOut]:\n2984:     # Diagnostic mode requires the pipeline path for score introspection\n2985:     if _USE_PIPELINE_SEARCH or diagnostic:\n2986:         return await _search_memories_pipeline(\n2987:             db,\n2988:             tenant_id,\n2989:             query,\n2990:             fleet_ids=fleet_ids,\n2991:             filter_agent_id=filter_agent_id,\n2992:             caller_agent_id=caller_agent_id,\n2993:             memory_type_filter=memory_type_filter,\n2994:             status_filter=status_filter,\n2995:             valid_at=valid_at,\n2996:             top_k=top_k,\n2997:             recall_boost=recall_boost,\n2998:             graph_expand=graph_expand,\n2999:             tenant_config=tenant_config,\n3000:             search_profile=search_profile,\n3001:             diagnostic=diagnostic,\n3002:             diagnostic_ctx=diagnostic_ctx,\n3003:             readable_tenant_ids=readable_tenant_ids,\n3004:         )\n3005:     logger.warning(\"legacy search path invoked; this path is deprecated and scheduled for removal\")\n3006:     return await _search_memories_legacy(\n3007:         db,\n3008:         tenant_id,\n3009:         query,\n3010:         fleet_ids=fleet_ids,\n3011:         filter_agent_id=filter_agent_id,\n3012:         caller_agent_id=caller_agent_id,\n3013:         memory_type_filter=memory_type_filter,\n3014:         status_filter=status_filter,\n3015:         valid_at=valid_at,\n3016:         top_k=top_k,\n3017:         recall_boost=recall_boost,\n3018:         graph_expand=graph_expand,\n3019:         tenant_config=tenant_config,\n3020:         search_profile=search_profile,\n3021:     )\n3022: \n3023: \n3024: async def _search_memories_pipeline(\n3025:     db: AsyncSession,\n3026:     tenant_id: str,\n3027:     query: str,\n3028:     fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n3029:     filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n3030:     caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n3031:     memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n3032:     status_filter: str | None = None,\n3033:     valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n3034:     top_k: int = DEFAULT_SEARCH_TOP_K,\n3035:     recall_boost: bool = True,\n3036:     graph_expand: bool = True,\n3037:     tenant_config=None,\n3038:     search_profile: dict | None = None,\n3039:     diagnostic: bool = False,\n3040:     diagnostic_ctx: dict | None = None,\n3041:     readable_tenant_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n3042: ) -> list[MemoryOut]:\n3043:     \"\"\"Pipeline-based search_memories -- same logic, decomposed into timed steps.\"\"\"\n3044:     from core_api.pipeline.compositions.search import build_search_pipeline\n3045:     from core_api.pipeline.context import PipelineContext\n3046: \n3047:     ctx = PipelineContext(\n3048:         db=db,\n3049:         data={\n3050:             \"query\": query,\n3051:             \"tenant_id\": tenant_id,\n3052:             \"fleet_ids\": fleet_ids,\n3053:             \"filter_agent_id\": filter_agent_id,\n3054:             \"caller_agent_id\": caller_agent_id,\n3055:             \"memory_type_filter\": memory_type_filter,\n3056:             \"status_filter\": status_filter,\n3057:             \"valid_at\": valid_at,\n3058:             \"top_k\": top_k,\n3059:             \"recall_boost_enabled\": recall_boost,\n3060:             \"graph_expand\": graph_expand,\n3061:             \"tenant_config\": tenant_config,\n3062:             \"search_profile\": search_profile,\n3063:             \"diagnostic\": diagnostic,\n3064:             \"readable_tenant_ids\": readable_tenant_ids,\n3065:         },\n3066:         tenant_config=tenant_config,\n3067:     )\n3068: \n3069:     pipeline = build_search_pipeline()\n3070:     result = await pipeline.run(ctx)\n3071: \n3072:     if result.failed:\n3073:         from core_api.pipeline.step import StepOutcome\n3074: \n3075:         failed_steps = [s for s in result.steps if s.outcome == StepOutcome.FAILED]\n3076:         if failed_steps and failed_steps[-1].error:\n3077:             logger.error(\n3078:                 \"Search pipeline step %r failed: %s\",\n3079:                 failed_steps[-1],\n3080:                 failed_steps[-1].error,\n3081:             )\n3082:         raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=\"Search pipeline failed unexpectedly\")\n3083: \n3084:     if diagnostic and diagnostic_ctx is not None:\n3085:         diagnostic_ctx[\"all_candidates\"] = ctx.data.get(\"diagnostic_results\", [])\n3086:         diagnostic_ctx[\"search_params\"] = ctx.data.get(\"search_params\", {})\n3087:         diagnostic_ctx[\"retrieval_strategy\"] = (\n3088:             ctx.data[\"retrieval_plan\"].strategy.value if ctx.data.get(\"retrieval_plan\") else None\n3089:         )\n3090:         diagnostic_ctx[\"diagnostic_original_top_k\"] = ctx.data.get(\"diagnostic_original_top_k\")\n3091: \n3092:     return ctx.data[\"results\"]\n3093: \n3094: \n3095: async def _search_memories_legacy(\n3096:     db: AsyncSession,\n3097:     tenant_id: str,\n3098:     query: str,\n3099:     fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n3100:     filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n3101:     caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n3102:     memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n3103:     status_filter: str | None = None,\n3104:     valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n3105:     top_k: int = DEFAULT_SEARCH_TOP_K,\n3106:     recall_boost: bool = True,\n3107:     graph_expand: bool = True,\n3108:     tenant_config=None,\n3109:     search_profile: dict | None = None,\n3110: ) -> list[MemoryOut]:\n3111:     \"\"\"Legacy search -- uses scored_search storage API endpoint.\"\"\"\n3112:     sc = get_storage_client()\n3113: \n3114:     # Resolve per-agent search profile with fallback to constants\n3115:     from core_api.services.organization_settings import validate_search_profile\n3116: \n3117:     sp = validate_search_profile(search_profile) if search_profile else {}\n3118:     _top_k = sp.get(\"top_k\", top_k)\n3119:     _min_similarity = sp.get(\"min_similarity\", MIN_SEARCH_SIMILARITY)\n3120:     _fts_weight = sp[\"fts_weight\"] if \"fts_weight\" in sp else _adaptive_fts_weight(query)\n3121:     _freshness_floor = sp.get(\"freshness_floor\", FRESHNESS_FLOOR)\n3122:     _freshness_decay_days = sp.get(\"freshness_decay_days\", FRESHNESS_DECAY_DAYS)\n3123:     _recall_boost_cap = sp.get(\"recall_boost_cap\", RECALL_BOOST_CAP)\n3124:     _recall_decay_window_days = sp.get(\"recall_decay_window_days\", RECALL_DECAY_WINDOW_DAYS)\n3125:     _graph_max_hops = sp.get(\"graph_max_hops\", GRAPH_MAX_HOPS)\n3126:     _similarity_blend = sp.get(\"similarity_blend\", SIMILARITY_BLEND)\n3127: \n3128:     # Temporal hint\n3129:     temporal_window = _extract_temporal_hint(query)\n3130: \n3131:     # Parallel: embedding + entity pipeline\n3132:     emb_task = asyncio.ensure_future(_get_or_cache_embedding(query, tenant_id, tenant_config))\n3133:     ent_task = asyncio.ensure_future(\n3134:         _entity_boost_pipeline(db, query, tenant_id, fleet_ids, graph_expand, _graph_max_hops)\n3135:     )\n3136:     try:\n3137:         embedding, (boosted_memory_ids, memory_boost_factor) = await asyncio.gather(emb_task, ent_task)\n3138:     except TimeoutError:\n3139:         emb_task.cancel()\n3140:         ent_task.cancel()\n3141:         raise HTTPException(status_code=504, detail=\"Search embedding timed out\")\n3142:     except ValueError as exc:\n3143:         emb_task.cancel()\n3144:         ent_task.cancel()\n3145:         raise HTTPException(status_code=503, detail=str(exc))\n3146:     except Exception:\n3147:         emb_task.cancel()\n3148:         ent_task.cancel()\n3149:         raise\n3150: \n3151:     # Overfetch so post-filter has headroom to drop low-vec_sim rows without\n3152:     # starving the final result set. Mirrors pipeline ExecuteScoredSearch behavior.\n3153:     _overfetch_top_k = _top_k * SEARCH_OVERFETCH_FACTOR\n3154: \n3155:     # Use scored_search storage API endpoint\n3156:     search_data = {\n3157:         \"tenant_id\": tenant_id,\n3158:         \"embedding\": embedding,\n3159:         \"query\": query,\n3160:         \"fleet_ids\": fleet_ids,\n3161:         \"filter_agent_id\": filter_agent_id,\n3162:         \"caller_agent_id\": caller_agent_id,\n3163:         \"memory_type_filter\": memory_type_filter,\n3164:         \"status_filter\": status_filter,\n3165:         \"valid_at\": valid_at.isoformat() if valid_at else None,\n3166:         \"top_k\": _overfetch_top_k,\n3167:         \"min_similarity\": _min_similarity,\n3168:         \"fts_weight\": _fts_weight,\n3169:         \"freshness_floor\": _freshness_floor,\n3170:         \"freshness_decay_days\": _freshness_decay_days,\n3171:         \"recall_boost_enabled\": recall_boost,\n3172:         \"recall_boost_cap\": _recall_boost_cap,\n3173:         \"recall_decay_window_days\": _recall_decay_window_days,\n3174:         \"similarity_blend\": _similarity_blend,\n3175:         \"temporal_window_days\": temporal_window.days if temporal_window else None,\n3176:         \"boosted_memory_ids\": {str(mid): factor for mid, factor in memory_boost_factor.items()}\n3177:         if memory_boost_factor\n3178:         else None,\n3179:     }\n3180: \n3181:     # CAURA-602 follow-up: per-tenant search bulkhead at the storage\n3182:     # roundtrip. The route-entry slot was already held above; this slot\n3183:     # bounds how many of one tenant's searches occupy storage-reader\n3184:     # connections simultaneously, preserving cold-tenant search latency\n3185:     # under a hot-tenant storm.\n3186:     async with per_tenant_storage_slot(\"storage_search\", tenant_id):\n3187:         rows = await sc.scored_search(search_data)\n3188: \n3189:     # Post-filter by min_similarity, then trim to top_k. The `vec_sim is None`\n3190:     # branch is defensive: the scored_search SQL currently enforces\n3191:     # `Memory.embedding IS NOT NULL` and the storage layer coerces None → 0.0,\n3192:     # so this branch is never taken today. Left in place — mirrored in the\n3193:     # pipeline post_filter step — so that FTS-only rows aren't silently gated\n3194:     # out by the cosine threshold if either invariant ever changes.\n3195:     rows = [r for r in rows if r.get(\"vec_sim\") is None or float(r[\"vec_sim\"]) >= _min_similarity]\n3196:     rows = rows[:_top_k]\n3197: \n3198:     # Build results from storage API response\n3199:     memory_ids = [row.get(\"id\") for row in rows if row.get(\"id\")]\n3200: \n3201:     # Fetch entity links for all result memories\n3202:     links_data = (\n3203:         await sc.get_entity_links_for_memories([str(mid) for mid in memory_ids]) if memory_ids else {}\n3204:     )\n3205: \n3206:     results = []\n3207:     for row in rows:\n3208:         mid = row.get(\"id\")\n3209:         mid_str = str(mid)\n3210:         entity_links = [\n3211:             EntityLinkOut(entity_id=el.get(\"entity_id\"), role=el.get(\"role\"))\n3212:             for el in links_data.get(mid_str, [])\n3213:         ]\n3214:         results.append(\n3215:             _dict_to_memory_out(\n3216:                 row,\n3217:                 entity_links=entity_links,\n3218:                 similarity=round(float(row.get(\"score\", 0)), 4) if row.get(\"score\") is not None else None,\n3219:             )\n3220:         )\n3221: \n3222:     # Increment recall_count and update last_recalled_at for returned memories\n3223:     _hooks = get_hooks()\n3224:     if memory_ids and _hooks.on_recall:\n3225:         try:\n3226:             await _hooks.on_recall(db, memory_ids)\n3227:         except Exception:\n3228:             logger.debug(\"Recall tracking hook failed (non-critical)\", exc_info=True)\n3229: \n3230:     return results\n\n(End of file - total 3230 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        return {\"start_date\": start.isoformat(), \"end_date\": end.isoformat()}\n\n    return None\n\n\nasync def search_memories(\n    db: AsyncSession,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    query: str,\n    fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n    filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n    caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n    memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n    status_filter: str | None = None,\n    valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n    top_k: int = DEFAULT_SEARCH_TOP_K,\n    recall_boost: bool = True,\n    graph_expand: bool = True,\n    tenant_config=None,\n    search_profile: dict | None = None,","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","text":"        return {\"start_date\": start.isoformat(), \"end_date\": end.isoformat()}\n\n    return None\n\n\nasync def search_memories(\n    db: AsyncSession,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    query: str,\n    fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n    filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n    caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n    memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n    status_filter: str | None = None,\n    valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n    top_k: int = DEFAULT_SEARCH_TOP_K,\n    recall_boost: bool = True,\n    graph_expand: bool = True,\n    tenant_config=None,\n    search_profile: dict | None = None,\n    diagnostic: bool = False,\n    diagnostic_ctx: dict | None = None,\n    readable_tenant_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n) -> list[MemoryOut]:\n    # Diagnostic mode requires the pipeline path for score introspection\n    if _USE_PIPELINE_SEARCH or diagnostic:\n        return await _search_memories_pipeline(\n            db,\n            tenant_id,\n            query,\n            fleet_ids=fleet_ids,\n            filter_agent_id=filter_agent_id,\n            caller_agent_id=caller_agent_id,\n            memory_type_filter=memory_type_filter,\n            status_filter=status_filter,\n            valid_at=valid_at,\n            top_k=top_k,\n            recall_boost=recall_boost,\n            graph_expand=graph_expand,\n            tenant_config=tenant_config,\n            search_profile=search_profile,\n            diagnostic=diagnostic,\n            diagnostic_ctx=diagnostic_ctx,\n            readable_tenant_ids=readable_tenant_ids,\n        )\n    logger.warning(\"legacy search path invoked; this path is deprecated and scheduled for removal\")\n    return await _search_memories_legacy(\n        db,\n        tenant_id,\n        query,\n        fleet_ids=fleet_ids,\n        filter_agent_id=filter_agent_id,\n        caller_agent_id=caller_agent_id,\n        memory_type_filter=memory_type_filter,\n        status_filter=status_filter,\n        valid_at=valid_at,\n        top_k=top_k,\n        recall_boost=recall_boost,\n        graph_expand=graph_expand,\n        tenant_config=tenant_config,\n        search_profile=search_profile,\n    )\n\n\nasync def _search_memories_pipeline(\n    db: AsyncSession,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    query: str,\n    fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n    filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n    caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n    memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n    status_filter: str | None = None,\n    valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n    top_k: int = DEFAULT_SEARCH_TOP_K,\n    recall_boost: bool = True,\n    graph_expand: bool = True,\n    tenant_config=None,\n    search_profile: dict | None = None,\n    diagnostic: bool = False,\n    diagnostic_ctx: dict | None = None,\n    readable_tenant_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n) -> list[MemoryOut]:\n    \"\"\"Pipeline-based search_memories -- same logic, decomposed into timed steps.\"\"\"\n    from core_api.pipeline.compositions.search import build_search_pipeline\n    from core_api.pipeline.context import PipelineContext\n\n    ctx = PipelineContext(\n        db=db,\n        data={\n            \"query\": query,\n            \"tenant_id\": tenant_id,\n            \"fleet_ids\": fleet_ids,\n            \"filter_agent_id\": filter_agent_id,\n            \"caller_agent_id\": caller_agent_id,\n            \"memory_type_filter\": memory_type_filter,\n            \"status_filter\": status_filter,\n            \"valid_at\": valid_at,\n            \"top_k\": top_k,\n            \"recall_boost_enabled\": recall_boost,\n            \"graph_expand\": graph_expand,\n            \"tenant_config\": tenant_config,\n            \"search_profile\": search_profile,\n            \"diagnostic\": diagnostic,\n            \"readable_tenant_ids\": readable_tenant_ids,\n        },\n        tenant_config=tenant_config,\n    )\n\n    pipeline = build_search_pipeline()\n    result = await pipeline.run(ctx)\n\n    if result.failed:\n        from core_api.pipeline.step import StepOutcome\n\n        failed_steps = [s for s in result.steps if s.outcome == StepOutcome.FAILED]\n        if failed_steps and failed_steps[-1].error:\n            logger.error(\n                \"Search pipeline step %r failed: %s\",\n                failed_steps[-1],\n                failed_steps[-1].error,\n            )\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=\"Search pipeline failed unexpectedly\")\n\n    if diagnostic and diagnostic_ctx is not None:\n        diagnostic_ctx[\"all_candidates\"] = ctx.data.get(\"diagnostic_results\", [])\n        diagnostic_ctx[\"search_params\"] = ctx.data.get(\"search_params\", {})\n        diagnostic_ctx[\"retrieval_strategy\"] = (\n            ctx.data[\"retrieval_plan\"].strategy.value if ctx.data.get(\"retrieval_plan\") else None\n        )\n        diagnostic_ctx[\"diagnostic_original_top_k\"] = ctx.data.get(\"diagnostic_original_top_k\")\n\n    return ctx.data[\"results\"]\n\n\nasync def _search_memories_legacy(\n    db: AsyncSession,\n    tenant_id: str,\n    query: str,\n    fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n    filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n    caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n    memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n    status_filter: str | None = None,\n    valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n    top_k: int = DEFAULT_SEARCH_TOP_K,\n    recall_boost: bool = True,\n    graph_expand: bool = True,\n    tenant_config=None,\n    search_profile: dict | None = None,\n) -> list[MemoryOut]:\n    \"\"\"Legacy search -- uses scored_search storage API endpoint.\"\"\"\n    sc = get_storage_client()\n\n    # Resolve per-agent search profile with fallback to constants\n    from core_api.services.organization_settings import validate_search_profile\n\n    sp = validate_search_profile(search_profile) if search_profile else {}\n    _top_k = sp.get(\"top_k\", top_k)\n    _min_similarity = sp.get(\"min_similarity\", MIN_SEARCH_SIMILARITY)\n    _fts_weight = sp[\"fts_weight\"] if \"fts_weight\" in sp else _adaptive_fts_weight(query)\n    _freshness_floor = sp.get(\"freshness_floor\", FRESHNESS_FLOOR)\n    _freshness_decay_days = sp.get(\"freshness_decay_days\", FRESHNESS_DECAY_DAYS)\n    _recall_boost_cap = sp.get(\"recall_boost_cap\", RECALL_BOOST_CAP)\n    _recall_decay_window_days = sp.get(\"recall_decay_window_days\", RECALL_DECAY_WINDOW_DAYS)\n    _graph_max_hops = sp.get(\"graph_max_hops\", GRAPH_MAX_HOPS)\n    _similarity_blend = sp.get(\"similarity_blend\", SIMILARITY_BLEND)\n\n    # Temporal hint\n    temporal_window = _extract_temporal_hint(query)\n\n    # Parallel: embedding + entity pipeline\n    emb_task = asyncio.ensure_future(_get_or_cache_embedding(query, tenant_id, tenant_config))\n    ent_task = asyncio.ensure_future(\n        _entity_boost_pipeline(db, query, tenant_id, fleet_ids, graph_expand, _graph_max_hops)\n    )\n    try:\n        embedding, (boosted_memory_ids, memory_boost_factor) = await asyncio.gather(emb_task, ent_task)\n    except TimeoutError:\n        emb_task.cancel()\n        ent_task.cancel()\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=504, detail=\"Search embedding timed out\")\n    except ValueError as exc:\n        emb_task.cancel()\n        ent_task.cancel()\n        raise HTTPException(status_code=503, detail=str(exc))\n    except Exception:\n        emb_task.cancel()\n        ent_task.cancel()\n        raise\n\n    # Overfetch so post-filter has headroom to drop low-vec_sim rows without\n    # starving the final result set. Mirrors pipeline ExecuteScoredSearch behavior.\n    _overfetch_top_k = _top_k * SEARCH_OVERFETCH_FACTOR\n\n    # Use scored_search storage API endpoint\n    search_data = {\n        \"tenant_id\": tenant_id,\n        \"embedding\": embedding,\n        \"query\": query,\n        \"fleet_ids\": fleet_ids,\n        \"filter_agent_id\": filter_agent_id,\n        \"caller_agent_id\": caller_agent_id,\n        \"memory_type_filter\": memory_type_filter,\n        \"status_filter\": status_filter,\n        \"valid_at\": valid_at.isoformat() if valid_at else None,\n        \"top_k\": _overfetch_top_k,\n        \"min_similarity\": _min_similarity,\n        \"fts_weight\": _fts_weight,\n        \"freshness_floor\": _freshness_floor,\n        \"freshness_decay_days\": _freshness_decay_days,\n        \"recall_boost_enabled\": recall_boost,\n        \"recall_boost_cap\": _recall_boost_cap,\n        \"recall_decay_window_days\": _recall_decay_window_days,\n        \"similarity_blend\": _similarity_blend,\n        \"temporal_window_days\": temporal_window.days if temporal_window else None,\n        \"boosted_memory_ids\": {str(mid): factor for mid, factor in memory_boost_factor.items()}\n        if memory_boost_factor\n        else None,\n    }\n\n    # CAURA-602 follow-up: per-tenant search bulkhead at the storage\n    # roundtrip. The route-entry slot was already held above; this slot\n    # bounds how many of one tenant's searches occupy storage-reader\n    # connections simultaneously, preserving cold-tenant search latency\n    # under a hot-tenant storm.\n    async with per_tenant_storage_slot(\"storage_search\", tenant_id):\n        rows = await sc.scored_search(search_data)\n\n    # Post-filter by min_similarity, then trim to top_k. The `vec_sim is None`\n    # branch is defensive: the scored_search SQL currently enforces\n    # `Memory.embedding IS NOT NULL` and the storage layer coerces None → 0.0,\n    # so this branch is never taken today. Left in place — mirrored in the\n    # pipeline post_filter step — so that FTS-only rows aren't silently gated\n    # out by the cosine threshold if either invariant ever changes.\n    rows = [r for r in rows if r.get(\"vec_sim\") is None or float(r[\"vec_sim\"]) >= _min_similarity]\n    rows = rows[:_top_k]\n\n    # Build results from storage API response\n    memory_ids = [row.get(\"id\") for row in rows if row.get(\"id\")]\n\n    # Fetch entity links for all result memories\n    links_data = (\n        await sc.get_entity_links_for_memories([str(mid) for mid in memory_ids]) if memory_ids else {}\n    )\n\n    results = []\n    for row in rows:\n        mid = row.get(\"id\")\n        mid_str = str(mid)\n        entity_links = [\n            EntityLinkOut(entity_id=el.get(\"entity_id\"), role=el.get(\"role\"))\n            for el in links_data.get(mid_str, [])\n        ]\n        results.append(\n            _dict_to_memory_out(\n                row,\n                entity_links=entity_links,\n                similarity=round(float(row.get(\"score\", 0)), 4) if row.get(\"score\") is not None else None,\n            )\n        )\n\n    # Increment recall_count and update last_recalled_at for returned memories\n    _hooks = get_hooks()\n    if memory_ids and _hooks.on_recall:\n        try:\n            await _hooks.on_recall(db, memory_ids)\n        except Exception:\n            logger.debug(\"Recall tracking hook failed (non-critical)\", exc_info=True)\n\n    return results","lineStart":2960,"lineEnd":3230,"totalLines":3230,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-api/src/core_api/services/memory_service.py","time":{"start":1780727706074,"end":1780727706108}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05de074048d0847f016a23bf99effc819193b6cd9afb41bf22"}},"id":"prt_e9ba471d2001JW87qjeyP2rnSI","sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","messageID":"msg_e9ba44c4d0018BIWxCBC1Pg1is"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780727706110,"sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kGQC365pj74RWGaxLl8rnNa1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py","offset":850,"limit":410},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n850:         *,\n851:         fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n852:         caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n853:         filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n854:         memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n855:         status_filter: str | None = None,\n856:         valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n857:         boosted_memory_ids: set[UUID] | None = None,\n858:         memory_boost_factor: dict[UUID, float] | None = None,\n859:         search_params: dict,\n860:         temporal_window: timedelta | None = None,\n861:         recall_boost_enabled: bool = True,\n862:         top_k: int = 10,\n863:         date_range_start: str | None = None,\n864:         date_range_end: str | None = None,\n865:         readable_tenant_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n866:     ) -> list[SimpleNamespace]:\n867:         \"\"\"Execute the full CTE-based scored search with entity-link JOIN.\n868: \n869:         Returns a list of SimpleNamespace objects with attributes:\n870:         Memory, score, similarity, vec_sim, entity_links.\n871:         \"\"\"\n872:         boosted_memory_ids = boosted_memory_ids or set()\n873:         memory_boost_factor = memory_boost_factor or {}\n874:         sp = search_params\n875: \n876:         _fts_weight = sp[\"fts_weight\"]\n877:         _freshness_floor = sp[\"freshness_floor\"]\n878:         _freshness_decay_days = sp[\"freshness_decay_days\"]\n879:         _recall_boost_cap = sp[\"recall_boost_cap\"]\n880:         _recall_decay_window_days = sp[\"recall_decay_window_days\"]\n881:         _similarity_blend = sp[\"similarity_blend\"]\n882:         _top_k = sp.get(\"top_k\", top_k)\n883: \n884:         # -- Scoring expressions --\n885:         # CAURA-594: pgvector's `<=>` is strict — NULL in → NULL out. A\n886:         # bare `1 - cosine_distance` would therefore propagate NULL up\n887:         # through the similarity blend into `score`, and PostgreSQL's\n888:         # default `ORDER BY score DESC` sorts NULLS FIRST — putting\n889:         # every unembedded row at the TOP of results. The CASE forces\n890:         # a numeric value (0.0) and also short-circuits so\n891:         # cosine_distance isn't even evaluated for NULL rows.\n892:         # `has_embedding` below is the authoritative NULL-vs-orthogonal\n893:         # signal for callers — `vec_sim == 0.0` is ambiguous with a\n894:         # genuinely orthogonal embedding.\n895:         vec_sim = case(\n896:             (\n897:                 Memory.embedding.is_not(None),\n898:                 1.0 - Memory.embedding.cosine_distance(embedding),\n899:             ),\n900:             else_=0.0,\n901:         ).label(\"vec_sim\")\n902:         has_embedding = Memory.embedding.is_not(None).label(\"has_embedding\")\n903: \n904:         ts_query = func.plainto_tsquery(\"english\", query)\n905:         raw_fts = func.ts_rank_cd(Memory.search_vector, ts_query)\n906:         fts_score = (raw_fts / (1.0 + raw_fts)).label(\"fts_score\")\n907: \n908:         # CAURA-679: NULL-embedding rows fall back to `fts_score` alone\n909:         # rather than the `(1 - w) * 0 + w * fts_score` haircut that\n910:         # the unconditional blend would apply. The haircut multiplies\n911:         # the FTS signal by `fts_weight` (≤1), so an FTS-matching but\n912:         # unembedded row could rank below noise-floor-cosine embedded\n913:         # rows (vec_sim ~0.15-0.20 from high-dim sphere clustering),\n914:         # which then drop it past the `LIMIT top_k * overfetch_factor`\n915:         # cutoff. This protects the FTS-fallback contract for both the\n916:         # CAURA-594 deferred-embed window and any case where the embed\n917:         # worker fails permanently — the row stays discoverable rather\n918:         # than silently undiscoverable.\n919:         similarity = case(\n920:             (\n921:                 Memory.embedding.is_not(None),\n922:                 (1.0 - _fts_weight) * vec_sim + _fts_weight * fts_score,\n923:             ),\n924:             else_=fts_score,\n925:         ).label(\"similarity\")\n926: \n927:         anchor = func.greatest(\n928:             Memory.created_at,\n929:             func.coalesce(Memory.ts_valid_start, Memory.created_at),\n930:         )\n931:         age_days = func.extract(\"epoch\", func.now() - anchor) / 86400.0\n932: \n933:         type_decay = case(\n934:             *[(Memory.memory_type == mt, float(days)) for mt, days in TYPE_DECAY_DAYS.items()],\n935:             else_=float(_freshness_decay_days),\n936:         ).label(\"type_decay_days\")\n937: \n938:         freshness = case(\n939:             (\n940:                 and_(\n941:                     Memory.ts_valid_end.is_not(None),\n942:                     Memory.ts_valid_end < func.now(),\n943:                 ),\n944:                 _freshness_floor,\n945:             ),\n946:             (Memory.ts_valid_end.is_not(None), 1.0),\n947:             (\n948:                 age_days < type_decay,\n949:                 1.0 - (age_days / type_decay) * (1.0 - _freshness_floor),\n950:             ),\n951:             else_=_freshness_floor,\n952:         ).label(\"freshness\")\n953: \n954:         if recall_boost_enabled:\n955:             days_since_recall = (\n956:                 func.extract(\n957:                     \"epoch\",\n958:                     func.now() - func.coalesce(Memory.last_recalled_at, Memory.created_at),\n959:                 )\n960:                 / 86400.0\n961:             )\n962:             recency_factor = func.greatest(0.0, 1.0 - days_since_recall / _recall_decay_window_days)\n963:             recall_boost_expr = (\n964:                 1.0\n965:                 + (_recall_boost_cap - 1.0)\n966:                 * recency_factor\n967:                 * Memory.recall_count\n968:                 / (Memory.recall_count + RECALL_BOOST_SCALE)\n969:             ).label(\"recall_boost\")\n970:         else:\n971:             recall_boost_expr = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"recall_boost\")\n972: \n973:         base_score = (_similarity_blend * similarity + (1.0 - _similarity_blend) * Memory.weight).label(\n974:             \"base_score\"\n975:         )\n976: \n977:         if temporal_window is not None:\n978:             cutoff = func.now() - temporal_window\n979:             temporal_boost = case(\n980:                 (Memory.created_at >= cutoff, 1.3),\n981:                 else_=1.0,\n982:             ).label(\"temporal_boost\")\n983:         else:\n984:             temporal_boost = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"temporal_boost\")\n985: \n986:         # Soft date-range boost: multiplies the score for memories whose\n987:         # anchor date falls inside the query-extracted window.  Pairs with\n988:         # tighter padding in ``_extract_temporal_date_range`` — replaces\n989:         # the old hard WHERE filter so semantically strong out-of-range\n990:         # memories remain retrievable.\n991:         if date_range_start and date_range_end:\n992:             from datetime import date as date_type\n993: \n994:             from sqlalchemy import Date, cast, literal\n995: \n996:             from core_storage_api.config import settings as _storage_settings\n997: \n998:             temporal_anchor = func.coalesce(\n999:                 cast(Memory.ts_valid_start, Date),\n1000:                 cast(Memory.created_at, Date),\n1001:             )\n1002:             _start_dt = date_type.fromisoformat(date_range_start)\n1003:             _end_dt = date_type.fromisoformat(date_range_end)\n1004:             date_range_boost = case(\n1005:                 (\n1006:                     and_(\n1007:                         temporal_anchor >= cast(literal(_start_dt), Date),\n1008:                         temporal_anchor <= cast(literal(_end_dt), Date),\n1009:                     ),\n1010:                     _storage_settings.date_range_boost_factor,\n1011:                 ),\n1012:                 else_=1.0,\n1013:             ).label(\"date_range_boost\")\n1014:         else:\n1015:             date_range_boost = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"date_range_boost\")\n1016: \n1017:         status_penalty = case(\n1018:             (Memory.status.in_((\"outdated\", \"conflicted\")), 0.5),\n1019:             else_=1.0,\n1020:         ).label(\"status_penalty\")\n1021: \n1022:         # Soft currency factor: memories whose ts_valid_end is in the past\n1023:         # relative to valid_at are down-weighted instead of excluded.\n1024:         # Pairs with the removal of the `ts_valid_end >= valid_at` WHERE\n1025:         # clause below — one bad enrichment date no longer blanks a memory.\n1026:         if valid_at is not None:\n1027:             from core_storage_api.config import settings as _storage_settings_cf\n1028: \n1029:             currency_factor = case(\n1030:                 (\n1031:                     and_(\n1032:                         Memory.ts_valid_end.is_not(None),\n1033:                         Memory.ts_valid_end < valid_at,\n1034:                     ),\n1035:                     _storage_settings_cf.expired_currency_factor,\n1036:                 ),\n1037:                 else_=1.0,\n1038:             ).label(\"currency_factor\")\n1039:         else:\n1040:             currency_factor = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"currency_factor\")\n1041: \n1042:         if boosted_memory_ids and memory_boost_factor:\n1043:             boost_tiers: dict[float, list[UUID]] = {}\n1044:             for mid, factor in memory_boost_factor.items():\n1045:                 boost_tiers.setdefault(factor, []).append(mid)\n1046:             whens = [\n1047:                 (Memory.id.in_(mids), factor) for factor, mids in sorted(boost_tiers.items(), reverse=True)\n1048:             ]\n1049:             entity_boost = case(*whens, else_=1.0).label(\"entity_boost\")\n1050:             score = (\n1051:                 base_score\n1052:                 * freshness\n1053:                 * entity_boost\n1054:                 * recall_boost_expr\n1055:                 * temporal_boost\n1056:                 * date_range_boost\n1057:                 * currency_factor\n1058:                 * status_penalty\n1059:             ).label(\"score\")\n1060:         else:\n1061:             score = (\n1062:                 base_score\n1063:                 * freshness\n1064:                 * recall_boost_expr\n1065:                 * temporal_boost\n1066:                 * date_range_boost\n1067:                 * currency_factor\n1068:                 * status_penalty\n1069:             ).label(\"score\")\n1070: \n1071:         # -- Build scored CTE --\n1072:         # CAURA-594: NULL-embedding rows are admitted only if they also\n1073:         # match the FTS query — otherwise they'd rank on `Memory.weight *\n1074:         # freshness * ...` alone and could fill top_k slots with rows\n1075:         # that have no relationship to the query during a large backfill\n1076:         # window. `search_vector @@ ts_query` is GIN-indexed, so the\n1077:         # extra predicate is free for rows that already had to scan\n1078:         # the tenant/fleet slice.\n1079:         # Other paths (find_semantic_duplicate, find_similar_candidates,\n1080:         # find_neighbors_by_embedding, compute_health_stats) keep their\n1081:         # NULL guards — vector-pure operations where a NULL operand has\n1082:         # no comparable semantics.\n1083:         # `plainto_tsquery('english', '')` (and any whitespace-only or\n1084:         # stop-word-only input it normalises down to empty) returns the\n1085:         # empty `tsquery`, which `@@`-matches every non-NULL `tsvector`\n1086:         # — that would silently re-admit every NULL-embedding row when\n1087:         # callers pass `query=\"\"` or `query=\"   \"` (e.g. entity-only /\n1088:         # vector-only search modes), bringing back the displacement-by-\n1089:         # weight bug. Gate on the Python-side query string so the\n1090:         # operator is only emitted when there's actual text to match.\n1091:         _fts_guard = Memory.search_vector.op(\"@@\")(ts_query) if query and query.strip() else false()\n1092:         scored_stmt = (\n1093:             select(\n1094:                 Memory.id.label(\"mem_id\"),\n1095:                 score,\n1096:                 similarity,\n1097:                 vec_sim,\n1098:                 has_embedding,\n1099:                 status_penalty,\n1100:             )\n1101:             # Multi-tenant read predicate: when ``readable_tenant_ids``\n1102:             # is provided (cross-tenant agent key), reads widen across\n1103:             # the full set; otherwise we stay single-tenant for the\n1104:             # common case. Result rows still carry ``Memory.tenant_id``\n1105:             # so the caller can attribute each row to its source tenant.\n1106:             .where(\n1107:                 Memory.tenant_id.in_(readable_tenant_ids)\n1108:                 if readable_tenant_ids\n1109:                 else Memory.tenant_id == tenant_id\n1110:             )\n1111:             .where(Memory.deleted_at.is_(None))\n1112:             .where(\n1113:                 or_(\n1114:                     Memory.embedding.is_not(None),\n1115:                     _fts_guard,\n1116:                 )\n1117:             )\n1118:         )\n1119: \n1120:         if fleet_ids:\n1121:             scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(\n1122:                 or_(\n1123:                     Memory.fleet_id.in_(fleet_ids),\n1124:                     Memory.fleet_id.is_(None),\n1125:                     Memory.visibility == \"scope_org\",\n1126:                 )\n1127:             )\n1128: \n1129:         if caller_agent_id:\n1130:             visibility_filter = or_(\n1131:                 Memory.visibility == \"scope_org\",\n1132:                 Memory.visibility == \"scope_team\",\n1133:                 and_(\n1134:                     Memory.visibility == \"scope_agent\",\n1135:                     Memory.agent_id == caller_agent_id,\n1136:                 ),\n1137:             )\n1138:             scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(visibility_filter)\n1139:         else:\n1140:             scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(Memory.visibility != \"scope_agent\")\n1141: \n1142:         if filter_agent_id:\n1143:             scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(Memory.agent_id == filter_agent_id)\n1144:         if memory_type_filter:\n1145:             scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(Memory.memory_type == memory_type_filter)\n1146:         if status_filter:\n1147:             scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(Memory.status == status_filter)\n1148:         else:\n1149:             # Exclude superseded memories from default search results. The\n1150:             # contradiction detector marks the older row ``outdated`` (RDF\n1151:             # path) or ``conflicted`` (semantic path) and points the newer\n1152:             # one at it via ``supersedes_id``. Surfacing both would dilute\n1153:             # ranking with stale claims agents shouldn't act on. Callers\n1154:             # that need to inspect superseded rows pass an explicit\n1155:             # ``status_filter`` to override.\n1156:             scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(Memory.status.notin_((\"outdated\", \"conflicted\")))\n1157:         if valid_at:\n1158:             from datetime import date as _date_type\n1159: \n1160:             from sqlalchemy import Date as _Date\n1161:             from sqlalchemy import cast as _cast\n1162:             from sqlalchemy import literal as _literal\n1163: \n1164:             # Hard filter on the START side, compared at DAY granularity.\n1165:             # Future-dated memories can't answer past questions — but strict\n1166:             # timestamp comparison also excludes same-day memories written a\n1167:             # few hours after the query was asked, which is too aggressive\n1168:             # for workflows where the question + its evidence share a day.\n1169:             # We cast both sides to DATE so same-day-later memories pass.\n1170:             _valid_at_date = (\n1171:                 valid_at.date() if hasattr(valid_at, \"date\") else _date_type.fromisoformat(str(valid_at)[:10])\n1172:             )\n1173:             scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(\n1174:                 or_(\n1175:                     Memory.ts_valid_start.is_(None),\n1176:                     _cast(Memory.ts_valid_start, _Date) <= _cast(_literal(_valid_at_date), _Date),\n1177:                 ),\n1178:             )\n1179:             # NOTE: the END side (`ts_valid_end >= valid_at`) is NO LONGER\n1180:             # a hard filter.  A past ts_valid_end now triggers the soft\n1181:             # ``currency_factor`` above (default 0.5x) — so an over-eager\n1182:             # enrichment date can't silently hide a semantically strong\n1183:             # memory from historical-question queries.\n1184: \n1185:         # NOTE: date_range_start/end no longer produces a hard WHERE filter;\n1186:         # the multiplier ``date_range_boost`` above handles it softly.\n1187: \n1188:         scored_stmt = scored_stmt.order_by(score.desc(), Memory.created_at.desc()).limit(_top_k)\n1189: \n1190:         scored_cte = scored_stmt.cte(\"scored\")\n1191: \n1192:         # -- Outer query: JOIN Memory + LEFT JOIN entity links --\n1193:         stmt = (\n1194:             select(\n1195:                 Memory,\n1196:                 scored_cte.c.score,\n1197:                 scored_cte.c.similarity,\n1198:                 scored_cte.c.vec_sim,\n1199:                 scored_cte.c.has_embedding,\n1200:                 scored_cte.c.status_penalty,\n1201:                 MemoryEntityLink.entity_id,\n1202:                 MemoryEntityLink.role,\n1203:             )\n1204:             .join(scored_cte, Memory.id == scored_cte.c.mem_id)\n1205:             .outerjoin(MemoryEntityLink, Memory.id == MemoryEntityLink.memory_id)\n1206:             .order_by(scored_cte.c.score.desc(), Memory.created_at.desc())\n1207:         )\n1208: \n1209:         # db_ms captures only pool wait + SQL round-trip; materialise rows\n1210:         # inside the session (they hold lazy-load handles), then drop the\n1211:         # Python-side grouping outside the measured block so OrderedDict\n1212:         # work doesn't inflate the DB timing signal.\n1213:         with db_measure():\n1214:             async with get_read_session() as session:\n1215:                 result = await session.execute(stmt)\n1216:                 rows = result.all()\n1217: \n1218:         grouped: OrderedDict[UUID, SimpleNamespace] = OrderedDict()\n1219:         for row in rows:\n1220:             mid = row.Memory.id\n1221:             if mid not in grouped:\n1222:                 grouped[mid] = SimpleNamespace(\n1223:                     Memory=row.Memory,\n1224:                     score=row.score,\n1225:                     similarity=row.similarity,\n1226:                     vec_sim=row.vec_sim,\n1227:                     has_embedding=row.has_embedding,\n1228:                     status_penalty=row.status_penalty,\n1229:                     entity_links=[],\n1230:                 )\n1231:             if row.entity_id is not None:\n1232:                 grouped[mid].entity_links.append({\"entity_id\": row.entity_id, \"role\": row.role})\n1233:         return list(grouped.values())\n1234: \n1235:     # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n1236:     # C-2) Load specific memories by ID (ENTITY_LOOKUP short-circuit)\n1237:     # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n1238: \n1239:     async def memory_load_by_ids(\n1240:         self,\n1241:         memory_ids: list[UUID],\n1242:         tenant_id: str,\n1243:         *,\n1244:         fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n1245:         caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n1246:         filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n1247:         memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n1248:         status_filter: str | None = None,\n1249:         valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n1250:         readable_tenant_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n1251:     ) -> list[Memory]:\n1252:         \"\"\"Load memories by ID with visibility/fleet/agent filters applied.\n1253: \n1254:         Used by the ENTITY_LOOKUP short-circuit in ``ClassifyQuery._collect_memories``,\n1255:         which already chose the specific memory IDs based on entity graph\n1256:         expansion and just needs them loaded — no vector cosine, no FTS,\n1257:         no freshness scoring.\n1258: \n1259:         No server-side ``top_k`` LIMIT: the caller has already capped the\n\n(Showing lines 850-1259 of 4754. Use offset=1260 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        *,\n        fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n        caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n        filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n        memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n        status_filter: str | None = None,\n        valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n        boosted_memory_ids: set[UUID] | None = None,\n        memory_boost_factor: dict[UUID, float] | None = None,\n        search_params: dict,\n        temporal_window: timedelta | None = None,\n        recall_boost_enabled: bool = True,\n        top_k: int = 10,\n        date_range_start: str | None = None,\n        date_range_end: str | None = None,\n        readable_tenant_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n    ) -> list[SimpleNamespace]:\n        \"\"\"Execute the full CTE-based scored search with entity-link JOIN.\n\n        Returns a list of SimpleNamespace objects with attributes:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py","text":"        *,\n        fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n        caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n        filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n        memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n        status_filter: str | None = None,\n        valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n        boosted_memory_ids: set[UUID] | None = None,\n        memory_boost_factor: dict[UUID, float] | None = None,\n        search_params: dict,\n        temporal_window: timedelta | None = None,\n        recall_boost_enabled: bool = True,\n        top_k: int = 10,\n        date_range_start: str | None = None,\n        date_range_end: str | None = None,\n        readable_tenant_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n    ) -> list[SimpleNamespace]:\n        \"\"\"Execute the full CTE-based scored search with entity-link JOIN.\n\n        Returns a list of SimpleNamespace objects with attributes:\n        Memory, score, similarity, vec_sim, entity_links.\n        \"\"\"\n        boosted_memory_ids = boosted_memory_ids or set()\n        memory_boost_factor = memory_boost_factor or {}\n        sp = search_params\n\n        _fts_weight = sp[\"fts_weight\"]\n        _freshness_floor = sp[\"freshness_floor\"]\n        _freshness_decay_days = sp[\"freshness_decay_days\"]\n        _recall_boost_cap = sp[\"recall_boost_cap\"]\n        _recall_decay_window_days = sp[\"recall_decay_window_days\"]\n        _similarity_blend = sp[\"similarity_blend\"]\n        _top_k = sp.get(\"top_k\", top_k)\n\n        # -- Scoring expressions --\n        # CAURA-594: pgvector's `<=>` is strict — NULL in → NULL out. A\n        # bare `1 - cosine_distance` would therefore propagate NULL up\n        # through the similarity blend into `score`, and PostgreSQL's\n        # default `ORDER BY score DESC` sorts NULLS FIRST — putting\n        # every unembedded row at the TOP of results. The CASE forces\n        # a numeric value (0.0) and also short-circuits so\n        # cosine_distance isn't even evaluated for NULL rows.\n        # `has_embedding` below is the authoritative NULL-vs-orthogonal\n        # signal for callers — `vec_sim == 0.0` is ambiguous with a\n        # genuinely orthogonal embedding.\n        vec_sim = case(\n            (\n                Memory.embedding.is_not(None),\n                1.0 - Memory.embedding.cosine_distance(embedding),\n            ),\n            else_=0.0,\n        ).label(\"vec_sim\")\n        has_embedding = Memory.embedding.is_not(None).label(\"has_embedding\")\n\n        ts_query = func.plainto_tsquery(\"english\", query)\n        raw_fts = func.ts_rank_cd(Memory.search_vector, ts_query)\n        fts_score = (raw_fts / (1.0 + raw_fts)).label(\"fts_score\")\n\n        # CAURA-679: NULL-embedding rows fall back to `fts_score` alone\n        # rather than the `(1 - w) * 0 + w * fts_score` haircut that\n        # the unconditional blend would apply. The haircut multiplies\n        # the FTS signal by `fts_weight` (≤1), so an FTS-matching but\n        # unembedded row could rank below noise-floor-cosine embedded\n        # rows (vec_sim ~0.15-0.20 from high-dim sphere clustering),\n        # which then drop it past the `LIMIT top_k * overfetch_factor`\n        # cutoff. This protects the FTS-fallback contract for both the\n        # CAURA-594 deferred-embed window and any case where the embed\n        # worker fails permanently — the row stays discoverable rather\n        # than silently undiscoverable.\n        similarity = case(\n            (\n                Memory.embedding.is_not(None),\n                (1.0 - _fts_weight) * vec_sim + _fts_weight * fts_score,\n            ),\n            else_=fts_score,\n        ).label(\"similarity\")\n\n        anchor = func.greatest(\n            Memory.created_at,\n            func.coalesce(Memory.ts_valid_start, Memory.created_at),\n        )\n        age_days = func.extract(\"epoch\", func.now() - anchor) / 86400.0\n\n        type_decay = case(\n            *[(Memory.memory_type == mt, float(days)) for mt, days in TYPE_DECAY_DAYS.items()],\n            else_=float(_freshness_decay_days),\n        ).label(\"type_decay_days\")\n\n        freshness = case(\n            (\n                and_(\n                    Memory.ts_valid_end.is_not(None),\n                    Memory.ts_valid_end < func.now(),\n                ),\n                _freshness_floor,\n            ),\n            (Memory.ts_valid_end.is_not(None), 1.0),\n            (\n                age_days < type_decay,\n                1.0 - (age_days / type_decay) * (1.0 - _freshness_floor),\n            ),\n            else_=_freshness_floor,\n        ).label(\"freshness\")\n\n        if recall_boost_enabled:\n            days_since_recall = (\n                func.extract(\n                    \"epoch\",\n                    func.now() - func.coalesce(Memory.last_recalled_at, Memory.created_at),\n                )\n                / 86400.0\n            )\n            recency_factor = func.greatest(0.0, 1.0 - days_since_recall / _recall_decay_window_days)\n            recall_boost_expr = (\n                1.0\n                + (_recall_boost_cap - 1.0)\n                * recency_factor\n                * Memory.recall_count\n                / (Memory.recall_count + RECALL_BOOST_SCALE)\n            ).label(\"recall_boost\")\n        else:\n            recall_boost_expr = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"recall_boost\")\n\n        base_score = (_similarity_blend * similarity + (1.0 - _similarity_blend) * Memory.weight).label(\n            \"base_score\"\n        )\n\n        if temporal_window is not None:\n            cutoff = func.now() - temporal_window\n            temporal_boost = case(\n                (Memory.created_at >= cutoff, 1.3),\n                else_=1.0,\n            ).label(\"temporal_boost\")\n        else:\n            temporal_boost = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"temporal_boost\")\n\n        # Soft date-range boost: multiplies the score for memories whose\n        # anchor date falls inside the query-extracted window.  Pairs with\n        # tighter padding in ``_extract_temporal_date_range`` — replaces\n        # the old hard WHERE filter so semantically strong out-of-range\n        # memories remain retrievable.\n        if date_range_start and date_range_end:\n            from datetime import date as date_type\n\n            from sqlalchemy import Date, cast, literal\n\n            from core_storage_api.config import settings as _storage_settings\n\n            temporal_anchor = func.coalesce(\n                cast(Memory.ts_valid_start, Date),\n                cast(Memory.created_at, Date),\n            )\n            _start_dt = date_type.fromisoformat(date_range_start)\n            _end_dt = date_type.fromisoformat(date_range_end)\n            date_range_boost = case(\n                (\n                    and_(\n                        temporal_anchor >= cast(literal(_start_dt), Date),\n                        temporal_anchor <= cast(literal(_end_dt), Date),\n                    ),\n                    _storage_settings.date_range_boost_factor,\n                ),\n                else_=1.0,\n            ).label(\"date_range_boost\")\n        else:\n            date_range_boost = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"date_range_boost\")\n\n        status_penalty = case(\n            (Memory.status.in_((\"outdated\", \"conflicted\")), 0.5),\n            else_=1.0,\n        ).label(\"status_penalty\")\n\n        # Soft currency factor: memories whose ts_valid_end is in the past\n        # relative to valid_at are down-weighted instead of excluded.\n        # Pairs with the removal of the `ts_valid_end >= valid_at` WHERE\n        # clause below — one bad enrichment date no longer blanks a memory.\n        if valid_at is not None:\n            from core_storage_api.config import settings as _storage_settings_cf\n\n            currency_factor = case(\n                (\n                    and_(\n                        Memory.ts_valid_end.is_not(None),\n                        Memory.ts_valid_end < valid_at,\n                    ),\n                    _storage_settings_cf.expired_currency_factor,\n                ),\n                else_=1.0,\n            ).label(\"currency_factor\")\n        else:\n            currency_factor = literal_column(\"1.0\").label(\"currency_factor\")\n\n        if boosted_memory_ids and memory_boost_factor:\n            boost_tiers: dict[float, list[UUID]] = {}\n            for mid, factor in memory_boost_factor.items():\n                boost_tiers.setdefault(factor, []).append(mid)\n            whens = [\n                (Memory.id.in_(mids), factor) for factor, mids in sorted(boost_tiers.items(), reverse=True)\n            ]\n            entity_boost = case(*whens, else_=1.0).label(\"entity_boost\")\n            score = (\n                base_score\n                * freshness\n                * entity_boost\n                * recall_boost_expr\n                * temporal_boost\n                * date_range_boost\n                * currency_factor\n                * status_penalty\n            ).label(\"score\")\n        else:\n            score = (\n                base_score\n                * freshness\n                * recall_boost_expr\n                * temporal_boost\n                * date_range_boost\n                * currency_factor\n                * status_penalty\n            ).label(\"score\")\n\n        # -- Build scored CTE --\n        # CAURA-594: NULL-embedding rows are admitted only if they also\n        # match the FTS query — otherwise they'd rank on `Memory.weight *\n        # freshness * ...` alone and could fill top_k slots with rows\n        # that have no relationship to the query during a large backfill\n        # window. `search_vector @@ ts_query` is GIN-indexed, so the\n        # extra predicate is free for rows that already had to scan\n        # the tenant/fleet slice.\n        # Other paths (find_semantic_duplicate, find_similar_candidates,\n        # find_neighbors_by_embedding, compute_health_stats) keep their\n        # NULL guards — vector-pure operations where a NULL operand has\n        # no comparable semantics.\n        # `plainto_tsquery('english', '')` (and any whitespace-only or\n        # stop-word-only input it normalises down to empty) returns the\n        # empty `tsquery`, which `@@`-matches every non-NULL `tsvector`\n        # — that would silently re-admit every NULL-embedding row when\n        # callers pass `query=\"\"` or `query=\"   \"` (e.g. entity-only /\n        # vector-only search modes), bringing back the displacement-by-\n        # weight bug. Gate on the Python-side query string so the\n        # operator is only emitted when there's actual text to match.\n        _fts_guard = Memory.search_vector.op(\"@@\")(ts_query) if query and query.strip() else false()\n        scored_stmt = (\n            select(\n                Memory.id.label(\"mem_id\"),\n                score,\n                similarity,\n                vec_sim,\n                has_embedding,\n                status_penalty,\n            )\n            # Multi-tenant read predicate: when ``readable_tenant_ids``\n            # is provided (cross-tenant agent key), reads widen across\n            # the full set; otherwise we stay single-tenant for the\n            # common case. Result rows still carry ``Memory.tenant_id``\n            # so the caller can attribute each row to its source tenant.\n            .where(\n                Memory.tenant_id.in_(readable_tenant_ids)\n                if readable_tenant_ids\n                else Memory.tenant_id == tenant_id\n            )\n            .where(Memory.deleted_at.is_(None))\n            .where(\n                or_(\n                    Memory.embedding.is_not(None),\n                    _fts_guard,\n                )\n            )\n        )\n\n        if fleet_ids:\n            scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(\n                or_(\n                    Memory.fleet_id.in_(fleet_ids),\n                    Memory.fleet_id.is_(None),\n                    Memory.visibility == \"scope_org\",\n                )\n            )\n\n        if caller_agent_id:\n            visibility_filter = or_(\n                Memory.visibility == \"scope_org\",\n                Memory.visibility == \"scope_team\",\n                and_(\n                    Memory.visibility == \"scope_agent\",\n                    Memory.agent_id == caller_agent_id,\n                ),\n            )\n            scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(visibility_filter)\n        else:\n            scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(Memory.visibility != \"scope_agent\")\n\n        if filter_agent_id:\n            scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(Memory.agent_id == filter_agent_id)\n        if memory_type_filter:\n            scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(Memory.memory_type == memory_type_filter)\n        if status_filter:\n            scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(Memory.status == status_filter)\n        else:\n            # Exclude superseded memories from default search results. The\n            # contradiction detector marks the older row ``outdated`` (RDF\n            # path) or ``conflicted`` (semantic path) and points the newer\n            # one at it via ``supersedes_id``. Surfacing both would dilute\n            # ranking with stale claims agents shouldn't act on. Callers\n            # that need to inspect superseded rows pass an explicit\n            # ``status_filter`` to override.\n            scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(Memory.status.notin_((\"outdated\", \"conflicted\")))\n        if valid_at:\n            from datetime import date as _date_type\n\n            from sqlalchemy import Date as _Date\n            from sqlalchemy import cast as _cast\n            from sqlalchemy import literal as _literal\n\n            # Hard filter on the START side, compared at DAY granularity.\n            # Future-dated memories can't answer past questions — but strict\n            # timestamp comparison also excludes same-day memories written a\n            # few hours after the query was asked, which is too aggressive\n            # for workflows where the question + its evidence share a day.\n            # We cast both sides to DATE so same-day-later memories pass.\n            _valid_at_date = (\n                valid_at.date() if hasattr(valid_at, \"date\") else _date_type.fromisoformat(str(valid_at)[:10])\n            )\n            scored_stmt = scored_stmt.where(\n                or_(\n                    Memory.ts_valid_start.is_(None),\n                    _cast(Memory.ts_valid_start, _Date) <= _cast(_literal(_valid_at_date), _Date),\n                ),\n            )\n            # NOTE: the END side (`ts_valid_end >= valid_at`) is NO LONGER\n            # a hard filter.  A past ts_valid_end now triggers the soft\n            # ``currency_factor`` above (default 0.5x) — so an over-eager\n            # enrichment date can't silently hide a semantically strong\n            # memory from historical-question queries.\n\n        # NOTE: date_range_start/end no longer produces a hard WHERE filter;\n        # the multiplier ``date_range_boost`` above handles it softly.\n\n        scored_stmt = scored_stmt.order_by(score.desc(), Memory.created_at.desc()).limit(_top_k)\n\n        scored_cte = scored_stmt.cte(\"scored\")\n\n        # -- Outer query: JOIN Memory + LEFT JOIN entity links --\n        stmt = (\n            select(\n                Memory,\n                scored_cte.c.score,\n                scored_cte.c.similarity,\n                scored_cte.c.vec_sim,\n                scored_cte.c.has_embedding,\n                scored_cte.c.status_penalty,\n                MemoryEntityLink.entity_id,\n                MemoryEntityLink.role,\n            )\n            .join(scored_cte, Memory.id == scored_cte.c.mem_id)\n            .outerjoin(MemoryEntityLink, Memory.id == MemoryEntityLink.memory_id)\n            .order_by(scored_cte.c.score.desc(), Memory.created_at.desc())\n        )\n\n        # db_ms captures only pool wait + SQL round-trip; materialise rows\n        # inside the session (they hold lazy-load handles), then drop the\n        # Python-side grouping outside the measured block so OrderedDict\n        # work doesn't inflate the DB timing signal.\n        with db_measure():\n            async with get_read_session() as session:\n                result = await session.execute(stmt)\n                rows = result.all()\n\n        grouped: OrderedDict[UUID, SimpleNamespace] = OrderedDict()\n        for row in rows:\n            mid = row.Memory.id\n            if mid not in grouped:\n                grouped[mid] = SimpleNamespace(\n                    Memory=row.Memory,\n                    score=row.score,\n                    similarity=row.similarity,\n                    vec_sim=row.vec_sim,\n                    has_embedding=row.has_embedding,\n                    status_penalty=row.status_penalty,\n                    entity_links=[],\n                )\n            if row.entity_id is not None:\n                grouped[mid].entity_links.append({\"entity_id\": row.entity_id, \"role\": row.role})\n        return list(grouped.values())\n\n    # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n    # C-2) Load specific memories by ID (ENTITY_LOOKUP short-circuit)\n    # ------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n    async def memory_load_by_ids(\n        self,\n        memory_ids: list[UUID],\n        tenant_id: str,\n        *,\n        fleet_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n        caller_agent_id: str | None = None,\n        filter_agent_id: str | None = None,\n        memory_type_filter: str | None = None,\n        status_filter: str | None = None,\n        valid_at: datetime | None = None,\n        readable_tenant_ids: list[str] | None = None,\n    ) -> list[Memory]:\n        \"\"\"Load memories by ID with visibility/fleet/agent filters applied.\n\n        Used by the ENTITY_LOOKUP short-circuit in ``ClassifyQuery._collect_memories``,\n        which already chose the specific memory IDs based on entity graph\n        expansion and just needs them loaded — no vector cosine, no FTS,\n        no freshness scoring.\n\n        No server-side ``top_k`` LIMIT: the caller has already capped the","lineStart":850,"lineEnd":1259,"totalLines":4754,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-storage-api/src/core_storage_api/services/postgres_service.py","time":{"start":1780727706077,"end":1780727706109}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05de074048d0847f016a23bf99f00881919c1acba765afc000"}},"id":"prt_e9ba471db001U3QE5TQvyvbgWg","sessionID":"ses_1645cad37ffeA4S42Sj1D0XYfI","messageID":"msg_e9ba44c4d0018BIWxCBC1Pg1is"}}
